title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Combine first three ingredients and form into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: bakery rolls
directions: Warm
the evaporated milk.
Add hot water.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and
salt.	Stir to dissolve the sugar and salt.
Sprinkle yeast over
the 1/2 cup of warm water.
Add the sugar and stir well. When yeast is dissolved, add to milk mixture.
Add oil with flour 2
cups at a time.	Beat well after each addition with
electric mixer.
Knead lightly, dough will be soft. Grease top of
dough with oil and cover.
Let rise to double, then punch
down.	Let rise
again.
Form	into desired buns, roll, kolaches
or cinnamon rolls.
Makes about 8 dozen rolls. Bake in 400°
oven
for about 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
These freeze very well.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dip chicken cutlets in flour.
Cook in margarine in frying pan.
Add peas with juice, mushrooms and white wine.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel eggplant and boil until very tender.
Drain and mash well.
In another bowl, beat the egg adding the sugar, salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Add mashed eggplant and mix. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: fisherman's casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
In saucepan, saute onion in butter. Add soup, milk, cheeses and seasonings.
Heat, stirring often. Thaw peas slightly to separate.
Combine macaroni, sauce, tuna fish (or shrimp) and 1/2 package peas, tossing lightly to blend. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Garnish with remaining peas.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all the vegetables in a large bowl.
Mix the salt, sugar, oil, vinegar and water.
Pour over vegetables and marinate several hours.
Just before serving, drain off liquid.
Serve salad on lettuce leaves or in a salad bowl.
It is delicious!

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: *This should be baked and cooled before starting the filling.

title: crab bites
directions: Cut muffins in half.
Mix all ingredients and spread on muffin halves.
(At this point they can be frozen for future use.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in quarters to serve.
(I like to cut each muffin half into sixths.) Makes 72 bites if cut in quarters.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Dredge each steak in seasoned flour.
Dip into milk and egg wash and dredge in flour again.
Deep fry and serve with cream gravy, the recipe of which is in the soups, salads, and sauces section of this same cookbook.

title: wheat bread
directions: Heat milk (water), margarine and honey to lukewarm (100° to 110°).
In a medium bowl, blend the yeast, salt and wheat flour. Slowly add liquid to wheat flour mixture.
Beat with spoon 200 to 300 times.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour at a time, until it is the right consistency to roll out (4 to 5 cups flour).
Knead, put into a greased bowl and let rise 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butter rolls
directions: Scald milk, stir in sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast in; stir well until dissolved.
Add lukewarm mixture, egg and 2 cups of flour, beat until smooth; stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover, let rise in warm place for about 30 minutes.
Punch down and shape into 2 dozen rolls.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake in hot 400° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Add orange juice, pineapple grapefruit juice and bananas.
Pour into appropriate freezer container and freeze.
About 1 hour before serving, remove from freezer.
Add 1 quart club soda per 2 quarts banana punch.

title: six-week bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, flour, soda and salt.
Cream together the shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs and buttermilk, blending together.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix well.
Mixture will fill a 5-quart ice cream bucket and will keep up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator.
Bake muffins at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, flour and sugar in medium bowl.
Add beaten egg yolks and 1/2 of milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining milk and vanilla.
In iron skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour pie filling into skillet and stir constantly on medium heat until filling has thickened.
Pour pie filling into already baked 9-inch crust.
Prepare meringue by beating egg whites, 1/4 cup of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie filling, making sure meringue covers pie filling and crust.
Bake in a 350° oven until meringue is golden brown.

title: pastry puff
directions: Takes 5 minutes to put together.

title: ralph's roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer, then sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Pour steak sauce and water over meat.
Marinate overnight. Bake at 350° covered for 3 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat butter in a small pan and saute the onions.
Combine cooked spinach, onions, milk, eggs and Mozzarella cheese in a bowl.
Blend well.
Turn into a shallow baking pan and sprinkle with both crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Place a layer of rice mixture into greased casserole.
Add a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Melt oleo, brown sugar and water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cut biscuits in half and children can make each into a ball and drop in sugar mixture; then toss them into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, children can "pick off" a biscuit.
Monkeylicious!

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini and sugar for 15 minutes.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir well and seal in jars.
Makes 5 pints.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil 1 1/2 sticks butter, 1 cup water and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Add flour, granulated sugar and salt. Beat in eggs, sour cream and baking soda. Pour in greased sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef and pineapple
directions: Cut up stew beef and onion; fry until tender in some oleo. Add water, Gravy Master, salt and pepper.
Add beef bouillon cubes, soy sauce and crushed pineapple.
Add flour and water mixture to thicken.
Serve on rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 5.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in Dutch oven.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery, mushrooms, zucchini, fresh tomatoes, herbs and salt.
Saute over medium heat until onion is soft; add can of tomatoes, tomato paste, honey and black pepper.
Bring to a boil, then simmer partially covered for about 30 minutes.
Add garlic and cook for 10 minutes. Add parsley last.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up slices of bread; place in greased baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch). Brown and drain sausage; spread meat over bread. Sprinkle with grated sharp Cheddar cheese. Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in baking dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.

title: turketti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix lightly with fork.
Place in 3-quart casserole; add or sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese over mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before baking or fix the day before.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until mixture starts to bubble.
Bake uncovered.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, peanut butter, and vanilla. Beat in sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in a prepared crust. Shave chocolate over top or drizzle with hot (bottled) fudge sauce.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pectin, in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in pectin; continue boiling 3 minutes longer, stirring frequently. Remove from heat; skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Quickly pour into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch head space.
Seal with 1/8-inch layer of paraffin and cover with lids.
Yields 7 half-pints.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Can be frozen.
Serves at least 6.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Measure cereal into large bowl; set aside.
Microwave chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in 1-quart microwavable bowl, uncovered, on High 1 minute; stir.
Microwave 30 seconds longer or until mixture can be stirred smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal in bowl, stirring until evenly coated.
Pour into large plastic food storage bag.
Add powdered sugar.
Seal bag; shake until well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.
Makes 9 cups snack.

title: no bake peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Coat with cereal or coconut.

title: grama rau's pepper stew
directions: Boil carrots until tender in 2 cups water.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: heavenly crunch
directions: Spread crackers on a large cookie sheet.
Sprinkle nuts over the crackers.
Bring oleo and sugar to a boil and then boil for three minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all but last 3 ingredients.
Place in large rectangular dish and top with chips, cheese and almonds.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Pour in ice cream freezer.
Fill with milk.
Freeze with ice and salt.

title: poached peaches
directions: Remove skins from peaches by dipping in boiling water, then transfer to ice water.
Heat wine and sugar until sugar dissolves. Add vanilla bean.
Halve peaches; cook in syrup 10 minutes over low heat.
Cool at room temperature.
Serve garnished with a cookie.

title: salmon rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in baking pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: skillet chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy skillet.
Heat slowly until the cheese melts.
Serve at once with hot rolls.
Don't overcook!!!

title: mick's deer chili
directions: Brown meat together. Add chili mix, tomatoes and Ro-Tel.
Let simmer for 1 hour.

title: sausage ryes
directions: Fry sausage and ground beef; drain well.
In medium size microwave-safe bowl, melt cheese on High, stirring often.
Combine melted cheese, spices and meats; mix well.
Spread on rye bread slices.
Place on cookie sheet and place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Drain the sweet potatoes and place in buttered casserole dish (9 x 9-inch).
Place apples on top.
Mix lightly.
Break butter and place on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry graham delight
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan crackers, oleo and sugar. Chill.
Prepare 1 container Cool Whip.
Whip and combine with cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: divinity
directions: Combine water, syrup, sugar and salt to cook to 234° on candy thermometer.
Add half of the syrup, 1 teaspoon at a time, to well beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue cooking other half of syrup until it reaches 270°.
Pour into egg mixture; beat until high gloss changes to dull.
Fold in vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Makes 48.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Combine sliced apples, cinnamon and 3 to 5 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, oil, eggs, salt and orange juice and beat well until batter is smooth.
Grease a tube pan and alternate layers of batter and apples, ending with a layer of apples on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours and 10 minutes.

title: cheese straws or wafers
directions: Mix butter and flour until it is the consistency of fine breadcrumbs.
Add grated cheese, cayenne and salt.
Mix lightly. Combine egg yolk, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and add the
egg yolk mixture to make a firm dough.
Pass through a cookie press (small star makes long straw) onto a cookie sheet or roll on lightly floured surface and/or cut into 1/2 x 3-inch strips.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
A special Christmas treat!

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water; chill until syrupy. Beat Milnot until stiff peaks form. Beat jello until foamy; beat into milk. Cream the cheese with sugar and vanilla; fold into milk. Fold in fruit. Add powdered sugar to crumbs; mix with butter. Place 3/4 crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Add cheesecake mixture. Top with rest of crumbs. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
Set shells aside.
Place pulp into a smaller mixer bowl.
Add cream cheese, chives, basil, salt and pepper; beat until smooth.
Add milk, beating until potato mixture is fluffy.
Spoon potato mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on baking sheet.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: paprika chicken
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown the onions in butter until transparent.
Add paprika and stir until reddish brown.
Cut the chicken into pieces and fry until brown all over.
Add the salt, chopped green pepper and tomatoes.
Add 2/3 cup water; stir well and cover with tight fitting lid.
Cook over very low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken spread
directions: Mix together well.
Chill at least 1 hour and serve with crackers.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and place on top.
Melt margarine and pour over top of crackers.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: pam's mexiloaf
directions: Mix ingredients together to form loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cheese may be sprinkled on top the last 5 minutes of baking time.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour.
Add broth all at once; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add chicken, peas and carrots and pimiento; heat until bubbly.
Line a 2 to 2 1/2-quart baking dish with pastry.
Pour chicken mixture into crust.
Add top crust and cut slits for escape of steam.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: walnut carrot cake
directions: Use 3 greased 9-inch layer cake pans.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until soft.
Remove from fire and spray with cold water.
When cool, remove skins and mash potatoes. Add eggs, pickle relish, celery salt, salt and onion.
Add mayonnaise to hold together; mix thoroughly;
chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Boil okra 5 minutes.
Brown meat until crumbly.
Drain and mix all together.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon cheese chiffon salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and boiling water in blender container. Cover and blend at low speed until jello is dissolved, about 1 minute.
Add ice; stir until partly melted.
Add cheese; cover and blend at high speed until smooth, about 1 minute.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Top with pie filling or fresh fruit.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, sugar, ginger, dry mustard and garlic, stirring to blend.
Marinate steak or chicken in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours.

title: italian cream cake(ella drgac's grand champion)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Let stand a few minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk, alternating with flour to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; fold in egg whites.
Gently stir in pecans and coconut.
Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured pans at 325° for about 25 minutes or until done.
Frost when cool.

title: kielbasa delight
directions: Cut kielbasa into 3 inch pieces & put in a large pan. Mix pineapple, chili sauce & brown sugar together and pour over kielbasa. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour 15 minutes. Baste frequently.

title: mini apple pies
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Flatten each biscuit to a 3-4 inch circle.
Combine the chopped apples, sugar, and cinnamon.
Place a tablespoon of the apple mixture on each biscuit.
Dot with a little butter.
Bring up the sides of the biscuit to enclose the filling and pinch to seal.
Place in ungreased muffin cups.
Bake for 11-13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate cake with chocolate sauce
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder. Combine oil and cocoa and add to dry ingredients.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Pour batter into a lightly oiled or nonstick sprayed 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle the remaining dry ingredients over the top of the batter one at a time, but do not mix.
Pour coffee or water over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
To serve, invert each piece on a serving plate.
Makes 9 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice with 8 cups of water.
Keep shaking it until water evaporates.
When rice is done, put Coco Lopez and Carnation milk and all ingredients in and let dry for at least 1/2 hour.
Put in plates and refrigerate for 1 hour, then eat it.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water in large bowl. Stir in sugar, salt and 1 1/2 cups water. Add eggs and oil; mix well. Add 6 cups flour, 2 cups at a time, mixing well after each addition. Knead in 1/2 cup flour on lightly floured surface. Place in large greased bowl. Let rise, covered, until doubled in bulk. Roll 1/2-inch thick on lightly floured surface;
cut with round cutter. Brush with margarine; sprinkle with sugar. Fold over; place on greased baking sheet. Let rise until doubled in bulk. Preheat oven to 375°. Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add milk and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in grated apple.
Coat skillet or griddle with cooking spray.
Heat to 325 degrees.
Use 2 Tbsp. butter for each pancake.
Cook on both sides.
Makes about 18 pancakes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: surprise cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Cream the cream cheese, egg and sugar and spread on thin bread; roll up as jelly roll.
Cut in half.
Roll in 1st, melted margarine, then mixture of 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°. Freezes well before baking.

title: sophie mueller's cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Slice very thin with a food slicer.
Place sliced cucumbers in layers in a bowl, salting each layer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
With clean hands, firmly squeeze out all the salted juice, squeeze 3 to 4 times.
Place in fresh bowl.
Add onion, cider vinegar, oil, dill weed and pepper.
Refrigerate covered 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: dark secrets(cookies)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread into a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 to 16 bars.

title: tasty rice
directions: Mix and put into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar,
shortening
and salt.
Add eggs one at a time. Add
flour and milk alternately.
Grease and flour cake mold. Bake
hour
and	20
minutes or longer (I bake 1 1/2 hours). Bake
at 325° in a cold oven.
Do NOT open oven while cooking.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Put both banana halves, 1 egg, 1 1/2 cups of milk and the sugar in the blender; blend until smooth.
Add ice and blend again.
Enjoy.

title: cherry cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add shortening, cherry juice, cherries and milk.
Beat 2 minutes and add egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in salt for 2 hours.
Make solution of vinegar and sugar.
Pour over cukes and pack in containers.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oil, eggs, and mandarin oranges.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle pudding over the pineapple. Stir. Add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled cake.
Refrigerate.

title: pudding dirt dish
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or in zipper-style plastic bag with rolling pin.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with a wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and half of the crushed cookies.
In 8 to 10 glass cups,
layer pudding mixes.
Top with gummy worms.

title: pecan pie with 90's twist
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt butter; add sugar and cocoa, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In large skillet, heat 4 tablespoons oil over medium heat. Brown chicken, a few pieces at a time, about 5 to 8 minutes on each side.
Add more oil if necessary.
Remove chicken to heavy 8-quart Dutch oven with cover.
In same skillet saute mushrooms 2 minutes. Add garlic, thyme, basil and parsley and saute 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Transfer to Dutch oven.
Pour brandy and wine into same skillet.
Scraping up brown bits, cook over high heat until reduced by half.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Baste chicken with sauce every 10 minutes.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute onion until soft in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add livers, garlic, bay leaf and parsley; saute 8 minutes or until livers are brown, but still pink inside.
Remove bay leaf and force the mixture through a sieve or puree it in a blender.
Beat in the remaining butter (reserving 1/4 cup) with the brandy.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into a crock or dish.
Melt remaining butter and pour over the pate to seal it.
Chill for 24 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: microwave chocolate-mint parfaits
directions: Place butter in a microwave-safe bowl; microwave at High 55 seconds or until melted.
Stir in chocolate wafer crumbs, mixing well; set aside.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into cakes. Brown in greased frying pan.
Serve with tartar sauce and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Take evaporated milk and put in bowl.
Then put in freezer until mushy.
Whip until thick.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs, vanilla, 1/2 cup sugar and melted margarine, mixed together.
(Save out 3/4 cup mixture for topping.)

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Prepare the Dream Whip or Cool Whip,
Mix pineapple juice, egg, sugar and flour together and cook as a pudding.
Cool and then mix into Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cold jello mix.
Can be made the day before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and pumpkin together.
Combine dry ingredients and mix with other mixture.
Grease and flour three 1 pound coffee cans and the 1 (16 ounce) pumpkin can.
Pour each 1/2 full or you can use 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from cans.
Cool 1 hour before slicing.

title: oreo cookie ice cream
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies.
Whip cream and fold in next.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or other 2-quart container.
(I use a glass loaf pan.) Cover; freeze 6 hours or until firm.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Make a custard of scalded milk, eggs, sugar and salt.
Add chocolate (melted over hot water) and vanilla.
Fold in bread crumbs.
Pour into pudding dish.
Dot with butter and bake in moderate oven 45 minutes.

title: spice cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves. Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and honey; beat well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Chill.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Dip half of ball into water, then into sugar.
Place sugar side up on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut wings at joints, using just first two sections.
Rub with fresh ground black pepper.
Fry in wok in peanut oil.
Drain when done. Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add hot sauce.
Pour butter/hot sauce over wings.

title: medivnyk(honey cake)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, honey and oil.
Mix well.
Slowly add flour, coffee, baking soda, baking powder, cloves and rum.
Beat well.
Blend in chopped nuts with spoon or spatula.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place in preheated oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend in egg.
Stir together flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten in one direction with fork tines; top each with a pecan half.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: *Can substitute any salad seasoning.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, 2 tablespoons butter, parsley, pimento and onion.
Toss lightly.
Heat soup, lemon juice, pepper and butter until bubbly hot.
Fold in shrimp and heat for 1 minute longer. Serve over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix all the remaining ingredients and add to jello.
Pour into an oblong dish and refrigerate until congealed.
This is really good with chicken or turkey or all meats.

title: apple delight
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add nuts and apples.
Pour mixture into a large greased pie plate.
Sprinkle some light brown sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Cover meat with vinegar, water, onions, bay leaf, cloves, salt, pepper and sugar.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator. Remove and wipe dry.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Place on rack in pressure cooker.
Strain vinegar mixture and add 1 1/2 cups to meat.
Cook at 10 pounds pressure for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool and thicken gravy with crumbled gingersnaps.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Simmer until thick.
Put in bottles and seal.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: trifle(low-fat)
directions: Prepare pudding with milk according to package directions. Slice cake and line glass container with 1/2 of it.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the fruit over the cake.
Pour half of the pudding on top. Add a layer of Cool Whip and repeat the four layers.

title: zesty breaded chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in melted margarine, then fiesta herb with red pepper soup mix, combined with bread crumbs. In a
13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan, arrange chicken. Drizzle with remaining margarine.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Heat oven
Oil bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan;
set aside. Place
egg whites in large bowl, beat with spoon until slightly frothy.
Add
oil and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Stir in sugar
and cocoa;
mix
well.
Stir
in
flour
until well blended.
Pour into
pan.	Bake at 350° for 22 to 26 minutes. Avoid overbaking. Cool before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Place 4 boneless chicken breasts in a large shallow baking pan.
In sauce pan, melt butter and stir in remaining ingredients and heat through.
Dump mixture over chicken and bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is golden brown.
Baste chicken frequently with sauce while baking.
Serve on rice pilaf.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Fry bacon and drain on paper towel.
Saute the onion in the bacon fat until golden brown.
Blend in the flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute and then stir in carefully the potatoes and bacon pieces, crumbled.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Melt butter. Crush crackers and add seasonings. Dredge chicken in butter, then in cracker crumbs. Place in baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: slow cooker pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil in skillet.
Transfer to slow cooker, along with the rest of ingredients.
Combine 1/2 cup water, 1 Tbsp cornstarch.
Stir into liquid in cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.
6 to 8 servings.

title: grilled sausage with cheese
directions: On grill, cook sausage.
Cut up in 3-inch links until done. Cut sausage half open and add enough cheese to cover exposed sausage.
Sprinkle bacon bits on after cheese has started to melt.

title: butterscotch pie(makes 2)
directions: Heat 2 1/2 cups milk.
Mix sugar, flour, other 1/2 cup milk, egg yolks and softened butter.
Add to hot milk and cook until thick (stirring as it thickens).
Put into baked crusts and top with beaten egg whites, sweetened.
Brown slightly to bake egg whites.

title: brick house plantation aspic
directions: Soften gelatin in tomato juice. Bring Bloody Mary mix to a boil. Remove from heat and add gelatin mixture.
Mix and stir until dissolved. Cool. Pour half of the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish which has been greased with mayonnaise.
Chill until congealed.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together well. Add to pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add a little more milk to make it a little more moist.

title: family favorite carrot cake
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, beat sugar, shortening and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and milk; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Spread into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Pop the corn in oil; set aside.
Boil for 5 minutes, 1 stick margarine, 1 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup Karo syrup and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Remove from heat after 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda (mixture will become foamy).
Pour over popcorn in large baking pan.
Bake at 275° for 1/2 hour.
Stir every 10 minutes. Pour onto wax paper and cool.
(Peanuts, pecans or mixed nuts may be added; mix through popcorn before baking.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Put the sliced apples on bottom of pan.
Mix the sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice and sprinkle over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Combine flour, eggs and milk.
Wash
and
clean chiles; cut into strips.
Cut cheese into blocks.
Wrap
cheese
with chiles; place in casserole dish.
Pour
batter
over
chiles. Pour tomato sauce over batter.	Bake at 350° for
hour,
or until bubbly and brown on the top.
Serve while hot.

title: cowboy bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ground beef, in crock-pot.	Layer ground beef on top.
Cook on high 1 hour and low 2 hours.

title: quick lasagne
directions: In saucepan, brown beef chuck, onion, garlic and oregano.
Add soup, water and vinegar.

Simmer 30 minutes, stir occasionally. In shallow 12 x 8-inch pan, arrange 3 alternate layers of cooked noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle each layer with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients to 238° (soft ball).
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add vanilla, walnuts and cherries.
Beat until just starts to thicken and pour into pan.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and freeze half.
Put other half in containers until ready to serve.
Add ginger ale when serving.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray only bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups with vegetable spray.
In bowl, beat milk, yogurt, egg whites, egg, vanilla and lemon zest.
In another bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Fold dry ingredients into wet until moist.
Stir in the apple.
Divide batter in muffin cups.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and place in casserole dish. Place boiled chopped chicken over broccoli. Salt and pepper. Mix 1/2 cup mayo with cream of chicken soup. Then add 1 cup chicken broth and mix with soup and mayonnaise. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with curry and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, bacon and onion in 1/2 cup milk in a 2-quart casserole dish for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups milk and cook 3 minutes.
When ready to serve, add grated cheese to the top of each bowl.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and stir in flour.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. May put fairly close together as they do not spread much.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: creamy orange salad
directions: Heat pineapple almost to a boil and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator. Stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip. Whip together. Chill in refrigerator.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, vanilla, flour and salt to eggs.
Beat with electric mixer.
Be sure flour is well mixed.
Heat skillet. Add teaspoon of butter to skillet.
Dip bread, a slice at a time, into batter.
Coat each side.
Drop bread into hot pan; cook 2 to 3 minutes per side or until golden brown.
Cut bread in half diagonally.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on toast.

title: grilled shrimp and scallops
directions: Thaw scallops and shrimp.
Halve the scallops.
Place the scallops and shrimp in a plastic bag; place bag in a bowl. Combine the oil, parsley, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper and pour over shrimp and scallops.
Seal the bag and marinate for 4 to 6 hours, turning bag occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade. Alternately thread shrimp and scallops on skewers.
Grill kabobs, uncovered, directly over medium coals for 12 to 15 minutes or until shrimp turn pink and scallops are opaque, brushing frequently with marinade, turning once or twice.
Or broil in oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: betty's baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender (low heat) and stir.
Add with bacon to remaining ingredients; mix well.
Top with additional bacon, if desired.
Bake uncovered in 1 1/2-quart casserole in 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
(I use the slow cooker; double the recipe and it works out great.)
Stir often.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Combine little more than 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Mix in 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk. Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Let cool slightly.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff, not dry; add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until forms stiff peak.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Pour 1/2 pudding over wafers and bananas.
Add another layer wafers, bananas, pudding.
Top with egg whites and bake in preheated hot oven at 425° until brown.

title: meatless vegetable soup
directions: Dice all vegetables very small.
Saute celery, onion, carrots and green pepper in butter for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook 15 minutes longer.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 3 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put in bowl and stir.
Bake 4 days at 200°; they burn easy. Makes 100.

title: pocket pizzas
directions: *You can substitute for different topping, depending on preference.

title: dilly dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until serving time.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and mango.
Mix with rest of ingredients and cook on top of stove for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder; sift together.
Add alternately with the sour cream and vanilla. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°. Bake for 1 1/2 hours all together.

title: meat pie
directions: In skillet brown beef, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add garlic powder and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Mix 1 box of pie crust and put on top of cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown. Put beef mixture on top of pie crust.
Mix other box of pie crust and top beef mixture.
Place under broiler and bake until browned good.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, reserve liquid.
In heavy saucepan, melt oleo; add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Gradually, add 3/4 cup liquid and milk.
Cook until thickened and smooth, stirring constantly.
The sauce should be thick; add milk and liquid if needed.
Add Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper.
Remove from heat.
Butter a medium-size casserole dish.
Layer asparagus, eggs, cheese and almonds.
Repeat the layers.
Spoon sauce over all.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly and brown.
Serves 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and cheddar quiche
directions: Defrost pie crust for 20 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Arrange 2 slices of Swiss cheese on bottom and sides of pie crust.
Put in 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese melts. Put pie crust on baking sheet while cooking.

title: ice cream surprise
directions: Allow ice cream to soften.
Crumble cookies and add to ice cream.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Pour into flat cake pan and freeze.

title: ada's meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and vanilla until frothy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until very stiff.
Fold in chips and cornflakes.
Drop by scant teaspoonful, well apart onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing to cooling rack.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Grease two 9-inch cake pans.
Prepare cake mix according to package direction using oil, eggs and juice from oranges.
Stir in oranges and nuts.
Spread evenly in pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: onion biscuits
directions: Melt butter in pan in 350° oven.
Stir in dry onion soup.
Drop quartered pieces of biscuits in pan and stir.
Bake for approximately 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once to coat all sides. This is a great appetizer.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder; set aside.
Mix eggs with sugar.
Add oil.
Beat 2 minutes (approximately).
Mix dry ingredients with egg mixture.
Add zucchini.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Fold in nuts and pineapple (optional).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour over half of dressing.
Put in pan. Place chicken and broth next.
Cover with soups and remainder of dressing mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Sort beans the night before and soak overnight.
Next day, rinse.
Cook beans (panboil) in about 1/2 teaspoon soda until skins break when blown on.
Rinse again.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until tender (2 to 3 hours).

title: pennsylvania dutch pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal. Beat water, egg and vinegar together; stir into flour mixture. Shape into ball and chill. Turn out on floured surface. Roll to fit pie pan. Will make (2)-2 crust pies or 4 single crust.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce mold
directions: Combine applesauce and Jell-O in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until Jell-O dissolves.
Cool to temperature.
Stir in 7 ounce lemon lime Sprite.
Turn into a 3-cup mold.
Chill until firm. Makes 6 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk.
Set aside for a few minutes. Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream together sugar, oleo and shortening. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add buttermilk and soda mixture alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites gently.
Then add nuts and coconut.

title: baked chicken with a twist
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side up, in a shallow 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cut bacon in 2-inch lengths.
Lay over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour off some of the drippings, if desired.
Blend soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Continue baking another 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: hot dip
directions: Put all ingredients except the dried beef in a blender.
Blend well.
Stir in the chopped dried beef.
Pour into a casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with pumpernickel bread or crackers.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger, stirring to break into small pieces until redness disappears; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with meat. Simmer.
Cook manicotti noodles according to package directions. Place a thin layer of sauce from jar in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fill manicotti noodles with meat mixture and place on top of sauce.
Pour remaining sauce on top
and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs and gradually add flour mixture.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Add chocolate chips to dough drops.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Using tablespoons of dough, makes 5 dozen.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 1/2 of the melted butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup butter with corn flake crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with parsley or lemon twists, if desired.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together juice from pineapple and cherries with instant pudding.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate.
Stir before serving.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Place shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs in a mixing bowl and beat.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to shortening mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: fruit pudding compote
directions: Pour milk and orange juice into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly on lowest speed for 1 minute.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip and beat 1 minute longer.
Arrange fresh fruit in a large serving bowl. Cover top of bowl with pudding mixture.
Garnish with 2 to 3 strawberries and a large spoonful of pudding mixture.
Must be kept refrigerated until ready to eat.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients for 15 or 20 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.

title: croissants a la vanille robson
directions: Bring the almonds to a boil; peel and crush them fine.
Add to flour, sugar and butter (cut in small pieces).
Add egg yolks; mix and knead quickly with fingers, hand to form an homogeneous mixture.
Form the dough into small pieces of 2-inches long and bend them in the shape of croissants.
Bake in a 350° or medium heat oven.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion until soft in oil; add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: kraut relish
directions: Mix drained kraut, green peppers, onions, celery, sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Mix well.
Let set overnight.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cranberry apple crunch
directions: Mix apples, cranberries and sugar.
Press into a casserole dish.
Mix margarine, oats, brown sugar, flour, salt and walnuts. Press on top of other mixture.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°. This will reduce in size some during baking.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add water; stir with wire whisk.
In separate bowl mix thoroughly the sugar, flour and salt, then add to mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Before filling crust, heat mixture until dark.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and let sit overnight to improve flavor.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: crosscut pickle slices
directions: Scrub cucumbers, using a vegetable brush.
Drain.
Slice into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices.
Add onions and garlic.
Add salt, mix thoroughly and cover with ice.
Let set for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly and remove garlic.
In large pan, combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil and add vegetables.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pack pickles loosely into pint jars (hot, sterile).
Adjust jar lids (held in simmering water until needed).
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Count time when water returns to boil.
Remove from water and set on folded tea towel to cool.
Makes 7 pints.

title: swiss broccoli almondine
directions: Cook broccoli until barely tender.
Drain.
Combine soup, thyme, almonds, lemon juice and rind and milk.
Add to broccoli and stir to blend.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.
May be prepared early, then refrigerated for baking later.

title: carnation custard pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar; add salt, vanilla, milk and water.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then lower to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: all-in-one tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, blend golden onion recipe soup mix with milk; stir in peas and carrots, cooked noodles and tuna.
Turn into a greased 2-quart oblong baking dish; then top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except confectioners sugar, together. Pour into greased pan.
Bake for about 30 minutes in a 325° oven. Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.
Cool; cut into squares. This is very quick, good and easy!!

title: wimpies
directions: Brown beef.
Add chopped mango, onion and chili powder; then add tomato soup diluted with 1/2 can water.
Then add spaghetti sauce and simmer for 2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Combine all, except potato chips and cheese.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 15 minutes; uncover and sprinkle chips and cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: texas hash
directions: Chop ground beef and saute with onion and green pepper until tender.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs; mix	well.
Sift the dry ingredients;
add
to
the egg mixture.
Add
the
mashed bananas and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put the cucumbers, onion and green pepper into a gallon jar. Bring to boil the salt, sugar and vinegar and pour over the cucumber mixture in the gallon jar.
Put jar (closed) in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 2 days.
Keeps forever.

title: pizza and calzone crust
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the yeast and sugar, then add the water. Let stand 10 minutes. In the food processor fitted with the metal blade, mix together the flour and salt. With the motor running, pour the yeast mixture through the feed tube and process until the dough pulls away from the sides of the bowl. Add the oil and pulse 3 or 4 times. Use right away or seal in a lightly floured plastic bag and refrigerate for an hour. Makes a 9-inch thick-crust pizza.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onions; lay pork chops on top of potatoes. Mix soup and water together; pour over all. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours.

title: mary's butter pecan ice cream
directions: Brown pecans in butter/margarine and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and churn ice cream as you usually do.
As ice cream thickens, add pecans, but wait until ice cream is fairly thick before doing this, otherwise the pecans go to the bottom.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, peas and beans; place in a bowl.
Add pimentos, green pepper and onion.
Set aside.
Place remaining ingredients in a pan and boil.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Leave overnight.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
More than 1 cup of buttermilk will need to be used.
Add the extra gradually until the mixture is of the right consistency.
It needs to be thick, not runny. Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french rice
directions: Combine

soup and butter. Drain mushrooms and water chestnuts; reserve liquid. Add water to liquid reserve to equal 1 1/3 cups. Add all ingredients together. Pour into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: corn bread or corn pone
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in small square pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and beat again.
Add flour and salt; mix to a cookie dough. Roll out about 1/8-inch thick and cut into shapes.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cookies should be beige in color.
You may ice them.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, bacon and onion.
Put all ingredients together and bake in ungreased casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Or cook in crock-pot.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours to give dill weed a chance to do its thing.
Yield:
1-quart.
Cut up celery, peppers, carrots or whatever to dip.

title: pasta and sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine sausage, spaghetti sauce, mostaccioli and Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday apple salad
directions: Cut fruit into bite size pieces.
Mix with nuts and celery. Mix with a small amount of Miracle Whip, more if you like it creamier.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Break up cranberry sauce in a medium mixing bowl and set aside.
Sprinkle gelatin over water in a small saucepan and let stand for one minute.
Heat over low heat until completely dissolved, stirring frequently.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: big chocolate chip cookies(yield:  50 4-inch cookies)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: veggie squares
directions: Press crescent roll dough onto 12 x 18 inch cookie sheet; bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing or soup mix; spread over crust.

Top with your choice of chopped veggies (for example peppers, onions, tomatoes, broccoli or cauliflower, chopped fine or shredded carrots). Sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Chill. Cut into small squares and serve.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: In a saucepan, make stuffing according to instructions.
Let cool for five minutes and set aside.
Place fillets on a cutting board and place 1 tablespoon of stuffing in center.
Fold fillet over stuffing and pin with a toothpick.

title: utah dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Use on baked potatoes, green salad, veggies, chips, etc.

title: filipino adobo
directions: Boil pork in vinegar, water, garlic, bay leaf, salt and peppercorns.
Remove and drain the meat when tender.
In a skillet, heat oil.
Fry meat until golden brown.
Serve hot with boiled rice.

title: hershey chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix and pour into greased and floured pan.
Cook 30 minutes or until done.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This dish can be prepared the day before and baked when you are ready to eat.

title: salmon roll
directions: Break salmon apart and drain.
Stir in first 5 ingredients. Shape
into a roll or ball.
Chill several hours.
Roll in parsley and pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Chill for several hours.

title: graham cracker cookie crunch
directions: In large cookie sheet, place graham crackers to cover pan. In medium saucepan, melt oleo.
Add brown sugar and heat until dissolved.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together the corn, sour cream, eggs, butter, salt, pepper and sugar.
Fold in the dry corn bread mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: yummy salad
directions: Stir ingredients into boiling water and cook until thick. When cooled, add the pineapple and oranges, fold in the Cool Whip.

title: vietnamese cookies
directions: First, crack 2 or 3 eggs and mix.
Add milk.
Then add flour and mix.
Add about 1/2 cup of sugar and mix.
Last, deep fry at 250° until golden brown.
(Oil should be 1 or 2-inches high.)
Get toothpick and poke in the center of cookie to see if done; may take longer.

title: jack-o-lantern pizzas
directions: Broil muffins until light brown.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of pizza sauce on each muffin.
Trim corners of cheese to make circles.
Cut Jack-O-Lantern faces on each circle of cheese with a paring knife. Place one cheese face on each pizza muffin.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add cocoa paste and milk.
Add sifted ingredients and vanilla.
Add nutmeats, if desired.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven until done.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: pretzel salad
directions: 1st layer: 1 c. crushed pretzels, 1/2 c. sugar, and 1 stick butter, softened.

title: crock-pot chicken italian style
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in the following order: veggies, meat and sauce.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or until meat is tender and thoroughly cooked.

title: dietetic pineapple cheese cake
directions: Put everything in blender.
Spray with nonstick cooking spray a 10-inch pie plate or round cake pan.
Pour batter in plate and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix together and stir until it starts to boil.
Remove from stove.
Double for more dressing.

title: perfection salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add sugar, salt and hot water. Stir until dissolved. Add vinegar and lemon juice.
Chill until it becomes syrupy, then fold in remaining ingredients. Turn into ring mold or individual molds and chill until set.

title: spicy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Dice onion.
Mix all ingredients well and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or white corn tostado chips.

title: meat casserole
directions: Cook beef and pork until tender, about 1 hour.
Add noodles and soup.
Cook about 20 minutes. Add cheese and onion.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Cover with corn.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hanky panks
directions: Scramble fry sausage and drain. Blend with cheese.
Put on party rye bread or biscuits. Brown in medium hot oven at 375°.

title: double coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir in cream of coconut and milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir hot mixture into egg yolks that have been beaten. Return to heat and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in oleo.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Blend first four ingredients with hand mixer.
If you would like a pineapple cheese cake, blend in crushed pineapple (20 ounces).
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 3 hours.
For a cherry cheese, just add cherries on the top.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine and simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain out spices.
Serve in bowl decorated with holly or other Christmas greens.

title: doc's cheese soup
directions: Saute carrots and onion in oleo.
Finely chop bag of broccoli and cauliflower.
Add vegetables and chicken broth to the stockpot.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cans of cream of potato soup and grated Velveeta cheese (I use approximately 8 ounces cheese). Simmer 10 minutes over very low heat.
Just before serving, stir in a small carton of sour cream.

title: fruity flapjacks
directions: Mix
pancake
batter
according
to
number of servings desired.
Add drained, diced fruit to batter.
If you desire a stronger
fruit
flavor, you can substitute the juice from the fruit instead
of
water
only in your pancake batter when you mix it.
Cook according to pancake box directions.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and raw bacon all together.
Put in baking dish; add ketchup, brown sugar, white sugar, garlic salt and vinegar.
Drain lima beans and kidney beans.
Add to pork and beans.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can use a slow cooker also.
Start on high for first hour and then turn on low for about 2 hours.
Remove cover for a while so it can thicken up some, 1/2 hour or longer.

title: recipe for love
directions: Mix well and spread evenly with tenderness.
Serve with smiles and laughter daily.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hacienda beef bake
directions: 1. Saute diced peppers in margarine till tender, set aside
2. Brown ground beef, drain, add peppers and stir. In
large bowl combine meat, corn, BBQ sauce, chili powder,
1/2 can of French fried onion rings.
3. Spread 1/2 the mixture into a casserole dish; spoon 1/2
the cheesewhiz in even dollups over the mixture. Spread
the remaining mixture into the casserole dish; spoon
remaining chhese whiz over the top.
4. Bake for 20-30 minutes till hot. Remove, sprinkle the
remaining French fried onion rings over the top. Bake
for 5 more minutes till onion rings turn crispy brown.

title: coffee cake #1
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie filling.
Spread half of mixture in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Spread pie filling over this evenly. Spread remaining batter evenly over pie filling.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or till done. Drizzle powdered sugar frosting over top while warm (1/2 c. powdered sugar, little warm water).
Favorite dessert.

title: caraway triangles appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for twenty-four hours. Spread on English muffin halves.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Cut in quarters before serving.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Combine melted oleo and flour; add next 4 ingredients.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes on simmer until celery is soft.
Add cheese and beer.

title: noodle salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together for dressing and chill.

title: garlic soy sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a jar; cover and shake until mixed well.
Ideal for broiling seafood, poultry and meats.

title: stuffed smoke sausage
directions: Cut smoked sausage lengthwise and place on a cookie sheet. Fill with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt, sugar and shortening to fine crumbs.
Add slightly beaten egg yolk mixed with ice water.
Mix together until a nice ball of dough forms.
Mixing does not make this dough tough, so all scraps may be used.
Dough can be frozen or refrozen. Divide dough into a ball the size for 1 crust.
Put into a Baggie and flatten.
Store in a container to freeze.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Let butter and cream cheese soften. Then cream together and add sugar. Mix until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, baking powder and flavoring. Mix well. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain and place in large pot. Add tomatoes, water, seasonings, corn and beans.
Simmer for as long as you want.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain fat.
Mix ground meat, cheese and soups.
Add onion rings.
Top casserole with more onion rings and cheese, as desired.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "no bake" cookies
directions: Mix in a pan:
sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Cook on medium heat and bring to a boil.
Once the mixture starts to boil, remove from heat and cool for one minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and quick cook oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup, peanuts and salt in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Stir after 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter or margarine.
Microwave for 2 more minutes on High.
Immediately stir in soda; stir until fluffy. Pour immediately onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: quick pizza
directions: Take bread
and put on tablespoon of Pizza Quick sauce; spread.
Add
pepperoni, then handful of cheese.
Bake in oven for approximately
minutes
or
until cheese is melted and brown.

title: mom's chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken soup, broth and tarragon; pour over chicken.
Arrange peas and carrots over top.
Mix flour and baking powder in a bowl; add buttermilk and butter.
Stir to form a thin dough; pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered about 1 hour until crust rises to top and browns lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel icing
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Gradually add cream.
Cook to soft ball.
Add vanilla and butter and beat until creamy enough to spread.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to hard boil. Remove from heat; add oats, nuts and vanilla. Mix well. Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: cheesecake
directions: Roll out 1 large can of crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Then add sugar and vanilla. Beat and add 1 egg at a time.
Pour batter onto crust and sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: good cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
When done, punch full of holes with toothpick.
Mix sugar and pineapple.
Cook until dissolved.
Pour over warm cake.
Cook pudding according to directions.
Pour over pineapple.
Let cool and chill.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Chill and serve.

title: cabbage and bow ties
directions: Saute onions and cabbage.
Cook bow ties pasta according to directions.
Combine; add sour cream and/or caraway seed to taste when serving.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix apples and sugar.
Add cranberries, carrots and nuts and stir gently to combine.
Mix dry ingredients and add to apple mixture; stir well.
Stir in eggs and oil and mix gently but thoroughly.

title: german (beer) coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and cloves; set aside.
Combine dates and nuts.
Stir in a small amount of the flour mixture, to coat; set aside.
In large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour mixture, alternately with beer, blending well after each addition.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out and cool.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix; bake in 13 x 9-inch pan; let cool.
Pierce with a fork and drizzle Kahlua over cake.
Chill, preferably overnight.
Break up cake and place half in large bowl (punch-bowl size).

title: duck with sauerkraut
directions: Wash duck.
Sprinkle
inside
cavity
with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix sauerkraut, water and sugar.
Stuff into duck. Cover.
Bake at 325°
for 20 to 25 minutes per pound or until tender and brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cream the pineapple, cream cheese and pineapple juice until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream, marshmallows and mayonnaise.
Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tortilla stack up
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas.
Begin spreading on tortillas and stack.
Top with crushed walnuts.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and warm water.
Let stand until yeast rises.
Mix remaining ingredients, stirring in enough flour to make dough stiff enough to knead.
Put into a greased bowl and grease top of dough to keep from crusting.
Put in a warm place until doubled in size.
Knead dough, adding enough flour to prevent sticking to hands.
Either roll out into rolls or refrigerate.
Grease top of dough.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil, buttermilk and beaten eggs to dry ingredients.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator and use as desired.

title: chocolate delight
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together cake mix, pudding, oil, water, sour cream and eggs together.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts until well blended.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake in 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick when inserted comes out clean.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef ribs.
Add frozen soup vegetables, stewed tomatoes, chopped onion, beef bouillon cube dissolved in water and 4 additional cups of water to soup.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add cut up potatoes.
Cook another 30 minutes.
Add more water as needed while cooking.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in pan and heat until margarine melts. Let cool.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to cooled mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken with salt and pepper for 3 hours.
Take out 1 cup of the broth, making sure to pick up about 4 tablespoons of the hot fat on top of the water.
Let water cool in a large bowl; stir in plain flour with a fork until dough is very stiff.
Roll out thin on floured area; cut dumplings into 1 x 3-inch strips. Remove chicken from water and debone.
Bring water to a boil. Drop dumplings into water, separating so each will reach water. Mix soup with milk.
When all dumplings are in water, turn down heat to simmer and cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Pour in milk and soup mixture.
Stir in.
Stir in deboned chicken.
Cook for 5 more minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms. Chop half of the stems in butter.
Add wine, onion powder and garlic. Simmer until liquid evaporates.
In another frypan, cook sausage. Add to stem mixture. Simmer 2 minutes. Add in bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Transfer mixture to a large bowl. Add minced spinach and grated cheese.
Stir well. Stuff mushroom caps. Arrange on cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rich crepes
directions: Place eggs in blender; whip to mix well.
Add salt, shortening, flour, milk and water.
Whip to blend thoroughly. Allow to rest 1 hour at room temperature before using.
Cook crepe in pan according to manufacturer's directions.
Yield: 36 (6-inch 15 cm) crepes.

title: souper burgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over toasted, open hamburger buns.

title: huckleberry upside down cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into lightly greased 9 X 13 pan.
Put berries over batter and sprinkle with sugar.
If using canned or frozen fruit, pour juice over it all. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: coconut squares
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Simmer, stirring constantly to soft ball stage or 238° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat; stir in coconut and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Allow to stand for 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and chill before serving.

title: cold fruit salad
directions: Cook vanilla pudding using only 1 cup juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges until mixture is clear and thick.
Fold in all fruit except kiwi and cherries.
Kiwi and cherries arranged on top are colorful for Christmas.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook noodles and broccoli as directed.
Set aside.
Melt butter and add crushed garlic.
Add soup and half and half.
Mix in noodles and broccoli and put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 minutes.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Cover bottom of a greased 9 inch baking dish with 1/2 the noodles.
Over these place the chicken,
celery and
onions. Combine the soup and milk and pour over the mixture in the pan. Cover with remaining noodles and cashews.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit bars
directions: Spread nuts on greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and flour. Mix well and spread over nuts. Cover with candied pineapple and cherries, cut in pieces. Bake for 1 hour at 275°. Cut in bars.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll in small balls.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add rolled oats and chocolate bits. Dough will be crumbly.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Partially bake 5 pounds chicken wings for 30 minutes.
Pour sauce over them and bake another 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Stir into corn meal and flour the onion, cheese and peppers before adding liquids and corn. Bake in tin pan at 400° or in glass pan at 375°. The corn bread turns out much better if cooked about 3/4 inches thick.

title: ants on a log
directions: Cut celery stalk in half and about 4-inches long.
Spread desired amount of butter or cream cheese inside.
Add raisins on top of the mixture.
Eat quickly before the ants crawl away!!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together
oil
and
sugar.
Beat
in
eggs, one at a time. Mix
in
pumpkin.
In
another bowl, mix together flour, baking powder,
baking
soda,
salt and all the spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Blend in nuts and drained raisins.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until it is set and firm.

title: quick hamburger and potato casserole
directions: In ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, blend potato flakes with sour cream and 1/2 cup water.
Mixture should be crumbly.
If not, add more potato flakes.
Pat firmly into bottom of pan.
Brown beef (with onion if using fresh); add to meat the second 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Spoon beef mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This recipe is easily doubled.
Serves 6.

title: jewish pound cake
directions: In a large bowl cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks and sour cream.
Mix.
Sift all dry ingredients separately 3 times and add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla; mix.
Make sure egg whites are stiff.
Fold carefully into mixture.
Grease chiffon pan and lightly flour.
If desired, chop 1/2 cup pecans and layer bottom before adding mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from pan immediately.
Cool.

title: raspberry fluff frosting
directions: Beat for a very long time (frosting gets stiffer and increases in quantity), probably about 15 minutes.
I serve this with angel food cake.
Cake can be frosted if it all will be eaten, but if not, I just pile some on each slice of cake.
The frosting keeps well until next day in refrigerator, but it soaks into the cake if kept on the cake.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Add nuts and bake 1 hour at 325° in Bundt pan.
Cool in pan.

title: golden salad
directions: Dilute jello and water; let cool.
Mix all together and then add jello.
Pat walnuts on top.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half.
Boil in water until peppers change colors.
Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Mix soup, rice and cheese.
Fill each pepper with meat mixture and sprinkle cheese on top of each.
Cook in oven for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender. Cool and dice.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in skillet until meat is browned. Add seasonings and tomato soup.
Simmer covered 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cook slowly, stirring occasionally until cheese melts. Stir in rice and cool.
Cut peppers into halves lengthwise; remove membranes and seeds.
Cook in boiling water covered until barely tender.
Drain and cool.
Place peppers on pan.
Stuff with rice mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
These freeze well.
Remove from freezer and partially thaw.
Cover with foil and bake.

title: piccolo pizzas
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Add oregano and garlic; set aside. Flatten biscuits to 4-inch circles and fill with tomatoes, then sausage mixture, then cheeses.
Top with olives.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: sangria
directions: In a punch bowl, combine wine, sugar and brandy.
Cut 2 oranges into eighths and 1 lemon into fourths.
Squeeze the juice into the bowl and let the fruit and wine chill for 2 hours.
After chilling, fruit can be removed or left in half and thinly slice the remaining oranges and thinly slice the lemon.
Float them on top.
Stir in Triple Sec and just enough ice to keep it cold.
Just before serving, add club soda; stir and serve.

title: satiny beige icing
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in saucepan.
Boil rapidly until syrup spins a 6 to 8-inch thread or 242°.
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites until stiff enough to hold a point.
Pour hot syrup slowly in a thin stream into egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Beat until icing holds its shape.

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add next 5 ingredients. Mix well.
Spread 2/3 of batter into greased cookie sheet.
Cover with lemon pie filling.
Drop remaining batter, by spoonfuls, here and there over pie filling.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot crab meat
directions: Combine crab, cheese and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce and onion to taste.
Put into a shallow baking dish.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: overnight salad
directions: Dissolve jello in one pint warm water; when cool, stir in fruit.
Let set overnight.
Slice and serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in pan. Boil 3 minutes. Add dry jello. Stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese, stir until well blended. Cool. Fold in rest of ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: italian casserole
directions: In glass casserole, arrange 1 layer hamburger, 1 layer potatoes, 1 layer onions and 1 layer carrots.
Continue to top of casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over top and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pull biscuits apart and put in a bowl. Add the cup of butter which has been melted.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Put in a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until insides are done.
Dump out.

title: prime rib
directions: Cover meat with all ingredients.
Cover with rock salt all over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 200° for 3 to 4 hours or if a large roast, bake 7 to 8 hours.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in oil, sherry and eggs.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack before removing from pan.

title: festive bean salad
directions: Combine beans and tomatoes in a large bowl.
Add peppers and sliced green onions.
Stir gently to combine.
Set aside.
Combine salsa, vinegar, cilantro or basil and pepper in a small bowl. Stir with a wire whisk until well blended.
Pour over bean mixture and toss gently.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: creamed peas and potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan; cover with water and cook until tender.
Cook peas according to package directions, adding the sugar.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a saucepan; add flour, salt and pepper to form a paste.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Add dill; cook until thickened and bubbly. Drain potatoes and peas; place in a serving bowl.
Pour sauce over and stir to coat.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water.
Mix all ingredients; save a little cheese and dressing mix to go on top.
Put in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corned beef
directions: Soak beef in water 1/2 hour or more.
Place on large sheet of foil and pat dry.
Pour water on and sprinkle spice.
Arrange orange and vegetable slices around meat.
Seal foil with tight double folds.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: english toffee
directions: Place piece of foil (approximately 10-inches long) on table before starting.
Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in sugars; add syrup and water.
Cook until candy thermometer reads 290°.
Add 3/4 cup pecans and cook three minutes more by the clock, stirring constantly.
Pour onto foil and quickly spread as thinly as possible.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top; spread when they melt.
Sprinkle finely chopped pecans on top.
Cool and chill, then break into bite-sized pieces.

title: christmas breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage.
Place bread in a casserole dish.
Blend eggs, milk and mustard.
Spread cooked sausage over the bread.
Pour the milk mixture over the sausage and bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill at least 2 hours.

title: zucchini bars
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add zucchini and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Mix well.
Add salt, soda, baking powder, flour and oats.
Mix until blended.
Fold in nuts. Pour into 15 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
