title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and bake in 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cool.

title: easiest-ever cocoa fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave confectioners sugar, cocoa, milk and butter or margarine on High (Full power) until butter is melted, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Blend vanilla and nuts.
Spread into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all together until well blended. Dough will be stiff. Roll into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Do not flatten. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: turkey-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange turkey in an ungreased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cook broccoli and place on top of turkey.
Cover broccoli with cheese slices.
Stir milk and soup together; pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix together meal, flour, onions, soups, sage, and eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Cool slightly.
Crumble bread; add broth and margarine.
Return to oven and heat until brown.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown meat, drain.
Put in crock meat, cheese, picante sauce and milk.
Heat on low for an hour or until cheese is melted. Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: potatoes and sausage casserole
directions: Cut potatoes up in quarters in a roaster pan. Coat with olive oil. Cut up garlic in slices. Add cut up onion. Add water and 2 lemons squeezed over potatoes. Sprinkle with oregano. Stir. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut up Italian sausage in chunks. After 30 minutes of baking, add sausage and stir. Sprinkle more oregano and squeeze more lemon juice over mixture. Bake for another 30 to 45 minutes until sausage is done, stirring often until done.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: gooy cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg, butter and pecans.
Press into a greased 9x13 pan.
Mix together powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over first layer.
Bake at 350 degrees about 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Grease the bottom of a glass baking dish and cover with slices of dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast in strips of bacon and place on the dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until fork-tender.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place chicken breasts on bottom of pan.
Put oleo on top of chicken.
Sprinkle garlic on top of chicken
and oleo.
Then mix in bowl the soups and milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place on top of chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Then uncover.
Then cook about 30 or 40 minutes until done, at approximately 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Add butter, sugar and allspice. Put in the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: nell's egg custard
directions: Beat eggs lightly; mix sugar and flour together; mix in eggs. Add other ingredients and pour into a pie shell (uncooked).
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then bake at 300° until knife comes out clean.

title: sausage ring
directions: Mix all together and shape into a ring.
Grease pan, then put foil on it and grease it too.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
When done, garnish with peaches.
Good for brunch.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let all soften; mix with mixer.
Roll in nuts.
Freezes well.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter. Add soups, shrimp, salt and pepper to taste. Stir in wine, curry powder and paprika to taste. Serve over rice.

title: "tipsy" tater casserole
directions: Place layers of potatoes, onions and celery into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle small amount of flour between potato layers. Add beer mixed with stock, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are almost tender.
Melt oleo and stir in crumbs, cheese and garlic powder. Uncover casserole and sprinkle top with crumb mixture.
Continue baking uncovered for additional 10 minutes or until top is golden brown and potatoes are tender.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips and Swiss cheese. Pour into a greased casserole dish and top with potato chips and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into thin strips across the grain.
Chop peppers, onions and water chestnuts.
Brown steak quickly in oil; remove from pan.
Saute peppers, onions and water chestnuts.
In separate bowl, mix the soy sauce, brown sugar, cornstarch and water. Combine sauce with steak and vegetables; cook for 3 to 4 minutes. Serve over rice.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Serves 4.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter and add sugars and water. Boil to 300° on candy thermometer.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and 1/2 cup chopped almonds. Spread in buttered cake pan 5 minutes.
Pour on chocolate chips and spread over toffee mix. Sprinkle on remaining almonds.
Cut immediately.

title: bread ii
directions: Let yeast, warm
water
and
teaspoon sugar set until bubbly. Meanwhile, melt 3/4 cup lard.
When first mixture is bubbly, add cooled (warm) lard, salt, sugar or honey and flour. Beat with beater good and knead well.
Let
rise
minutes
and knead until elastic.
Let rise until double.
Punch
down;
let rise again.
Makes 6 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30
minutes. Grease
and
cover
with
wax paper and cloth to steam.

title: mexican rice
directions: In a large pan saute rice and onion for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Add tomato sauce, chicken broth and spices.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is tender and fluffy.
Stir in corn and green onions and heat.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: mandarin orange congealed salad
directions: Thoroughly mix all the ingredients in a large bowl. Then chill. This makes
a lot of fruit salad. You may want to put in 2 containers.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain.
Dice onion.
Mix meat, onions, salts, basil, tomatoes and tomato paste in pan.
Cook 30 minutes. Cook noodles.
Mix cottage cheese, parsley, eggs, salt and pepper.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, oil and 2 tablespoons of water by hand. Mixture will be stiff and slightly crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture and pat remainder in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake crust at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lil's date nut bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, cut dates.
Add baking soda and boiling water.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg until smooth.
Add date mixture.
Combine well; add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: creamy mushroom sauce
directions: Combine soup, milk and sour cream in saucepan.
Heat, stirring, until smooth and heated through; stir in pimento. Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle in bottom of pan the chopped walnuts.
Layer with frozen dinner rolls.

title: green apple cake
directions: Mix the sugar and butter well and add the egg; blend all together.
Next add the cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Put in the chopped apples and the nutmeats.
Mix. Add the flour and the cocoa. Then add the baking soda, mixed with cold coffee and then put in vanilla.
Put it in a bread pan or small cake pan.
Preheat the oven to 350° and bake it for 45 minutes.

title: bacon-wrapped smoked sausages
directions: Cut bacon slices into thirds. Wrap each sausage with bacon and place in a foil-lined 10 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over sausages and bake for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples; set aside.
Place salad oil, sugar and eggs in bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add small amount of flour mixture at a time to creamed mixture.
Beat well when batter is stiff.
Add pecans and apples. Place in 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: subgum soup
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Cook celery and mushrooms 2 minutes. Add water chestnuts, bean sprouts, chicken and broth.
Cook on low for 10 minutes.
Add egg gradually, stirring steadily.
Serves 6.

title: yum-yum cake(low-fat, low calories)
directions: Pinch cake into small pieces and layer the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then spread pineapple, then mix pudding according to package using skim or 2% milk.
Spread over pineapple, then cut up bananas and layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: festive tortilla soup
directions: Begin boiling chicken broth.
Cut veggies; add to boiling broth.
Cut tortillas into rough 1-inch squares; set aside.
Boil 30 to 45 minutes.
Add spices and tortilla pieces.
Reduce heat to simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: speedy remoulade sauce
directions: Stir and chill several hours.
Serve over seafood.

title: almond poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease (or use cupcake papers) 2 (12-cup) muffin tins.
In large bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In medium bowl, whisk oil, milk, eggs, sugar and extract until well blended.
Slowly combine both mixtures and blend just until moistened.
(Do not overmix.)
Stir in poppy seed.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Mix flour and 1 teaspoon salt, coat chicken pieces with mixture.
Brown chicken on both sides in hot oil, put chicken in roaster and add green pepper and onion.
Mix tomato sauce, water, seasonings and mushrooms (with liquid).
Pour over chicken. Cover.
Place in oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 375° or until chicken is done.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese. Add 1 cup of pineapple juice.
Fold in pineapple chunks.
Pour this in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful 1 inch apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Before baking, place cherry on cookie. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove at once from baking sheet with moistened spatula.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time and blend well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with mixture of milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased and lightly floured large tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: supreme garden bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Boil vinegar, sugar and water together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately pour over all vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: apple and cinnamon sweet rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Combine cinnamon, apples, vanilla and artificial sweetener.
With rolling pin, roll the bread until flat.
Spoon apple and cinnamon mixture onto center of bread. Roll bread like jelly roll and fasten with a toothpick.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix strawberries and glaze, set aside.
Mix cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and set aside.
Cut cake into cubes.
Layer in large glass bowl.
Begin with cake layer, then Cool Whip layer, then strawberry layer. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with strawberry layer.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and milk and spread on the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place chicken breasts on top and sprinkle one package dried onion soup over all. Cover dish with lid or foil wrap and bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: snapper monterey(can substitute chicken for the snapper)
directions: Saute in a pan the butter, avocado, tomato, garlic, dill and white wine.
Now flour and egg the snapper and grill in a little butter.
Cook on both sides; top with avocado and tomato mixture. Cover with Jack cheese and bake in 550° oven for about 3 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Grate them and mix with other ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish until warm (20 minutes). Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: chunk ham fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine and set aside.
Cook peas and set aside. Prepare white sauce according to package directions with the milk. Stir in fettuccine, peas, ham and Parmesan cheese.
Stir to coat good and serve.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brush dirt from mushrooms. Remove stems and finely chop them (stems). Brown sausage, mushroom stems, onion and garlic. Stir to crumble. Drain. Roast red pepper over open flame (skin will turn black and peel off easily). Peel and seed red pepper. Finely chop and add to sausage along with bread crumbs. Stir to combine. Stuff mushrooms with sausage mix. Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve warm.

title: crab puffs
directions: Combine cream cheese, crab, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 teaspoon crab filling in center of each wonton wrapper. Spread small amount of margarine on two adjacent sides of wrapper.

Pinch in the middle, then fold down the opposite corners, forming wings. Deep fry in oil until golden. Drain on paper towels. Serve along with hot mustard made by combining mustard powder and water to desired consistency.

title: court bouillon au vin blanc
directions: Peel carrots and cut into slices.
Peel and thinly slice onions.
Cut celery into 3/4-inch pieces.
Pour wine into large saucepan and add water, carrots, onions, thyme, parsley, cloves, peppercorns and salt to taste.
Simmer for 40 minutes and leave to cool before straining.

title: honeyed pineapple ham loaf
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Drain the pineapple.
Cut the luncheon meat into 4 slices each, not quite through to the bottom.
Place in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix the crushed pineapple with the brown sugar and honey.
Spread this mixture between the slices of luncheon meat and over the top.
Stud meat with whole cloves.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy broccoli and chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place thawed and drained broccoli (do not cook).
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soups and mayonnaise together; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and season to taste.
Bake,
covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind or chop vegetables; sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight covered with foil.
The next morning, rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes approximately 9 pints.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Grate and mix cheeses.
Put 1/2 of the chilies on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish (or use 2 smaller dishes).
Layer about 3/4 of the cheese over chilies, then the other 1/2 of the peppers over cheese.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Beat together eggs, evaporated milk, flour and salt; pour over the cheese.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: caramel-brownie cheesecake
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs and butter, stirring well.
Press mixture firmly in bottom and 2 inches up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Let cool completely on a wire rack.
Combine caramels and milk in a small heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring often, until caramels melt. Pour caramel mixture over crust.
Sprinkle crumbled brownies over caramel.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and flour.
Cook 15 minutes or until onions soften and brown.
Simmer bouillon and water; add onions, cover and simmer 15-20 minutes.
Pour into oven proof bowls.
Place a slice of the toasted bread on top and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place under broiler to brown and melt cheese.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: quick and easy hamburger casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet and cook over medium heat, stirring until meat is broken up and browned and the onion and pepper are tender.
Stir in soup (undiluted), catsup and water.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with frozen potato puffs and bake in a 375° oven (uncovered) until puffs are golden brown, about 35 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and beer in a large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Spoon 4 tablespoons melted butter evenly over top.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Brush top with remaining butter.
Continue baking until top is golden and tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.

title: 24-hour layer salad
directions: *Use a creamy type of bottled salad dressing instead of the mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring last.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate crunch cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth and set aside. To 1 batch of chocolate cake batter that would yield 1 sheet pan, add almond extract and Oreo* cookie pieces.
Gently swirl in cream cheese mixture.
Deposit cupcake batter into lined 3 ounce muffin tins, using a No.
20 scoop.
Bake according to cake batter directions.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	In a large bowl, beat condensed milk, egg,
peanut
butter
and
vanilla	until
smooth.	Add Bisquick and mix well.
Chill for one hour.	Shape into 1-inch balls and bake 2
inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet, 6 to 8 minutes. Press Hershey's kisses in center of each cookie immediately after baking.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Remove skins from chickens.
Steam chicken for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool chicken.
Peel chicken from bones in direction of grain.
Tear chicken with hands into strips.
Mix chicken juice, water, soy sauce, salt, sesame seed paste and peanut butter.
On very low heat mix and stir until it boils.
Cool mixture.
Add vinegar and sesame oil.
Place chicken on shredded lettuce.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Serve.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat well and pour 1/4 cup of mixture onto middle of a flat, well-seasoned crepe pan.
Spread until whole bottom of pan is covered with liquid.
Brown slightly and flip over; brown other side.
Place pancake on plate and spread with butter/margarine and syrup (or topping of your choice).
Roll up, cut and enjoy!

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Add brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Put biscuits in muffin pan and make a well in each one.
Add mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° until brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and turn into one large (2 1/2 qt.) or two smaller casseroles.
Top with crumbled Ritz Crackers (1/2 stack). Drizzle 2 tbsp. melted butter over crackers.
(Can be frozen before baking, defrost to bake.)
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: short cut fudge
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Chill.
Place in small pan and when firm cut in small pieces.

title: mock pierogi
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add grated cheese to hot mashed potatoes until cheese melts.
Mix thoroughly.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix and put into a greased casserole (1-quart) dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Rinse seeds well and for each 2 cups of seeds, place in a saucepan with 1 quart of water and about 2 tablespoons of salt (most of salt will be discarded later).
Simmer for 10 minutes; drain well and pat dry on paper toweling.
Preheat oven to 350°. Toss seeds with 1 tablespoon melted butter in bowl until seeds are evenly coated.
Spread out on cookie sheet with sides.
Bake for 30 minutes, tossing occasionally until crisp and golden brown.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks and lime juice until creamy.
Fold in stiffened egg white.
Pour in pie crust.
Beat remaining egg whites; gradually add sugar and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Spread on pie and seal edges.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Thinly slice the potatoes and place in a shallow baking dish. In a small saucepan, heat butter, onion, salt, thyme, and pepper until the butter is melted.
Drizzle over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer or until the cheese melts.
6-8 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal squares
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in a saucepot.
Cook for 1 minute at rapid boil.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pan. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry souffle
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on cold apple juice; let soften.
Heat apple juice and gelatin until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat and add pureed strawberries and lemon juice; mix well.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites into gelatin mixture.
Next, fold whipped topping into mixture. Divide evenly into custard cups or parfait glasses.
Refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
Yields 5 servings.
Exchanges:
1 fruit and 1 fat.

title: french dressing for tossed salad
directions: Heat to dissolve sugar.
Taste and add more sugar if needed.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine dry ingredients. In large bowl, blend butter, eggs, vanilla and sugars until creamy. Gradually combine with flour mixture.
Add M&M's, saving small amount to decorate tops of cookies.
Grease cookie sheet and drop by teaspoonfuls on sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: super seafood salad
directions: Cut crab delights flakes in half.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving. Makes 2 cups.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread on bottom of 11 x 7-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order given.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix all together and make medium balls.
Roll in bread crumbs, then put in roasting pan.
Bake in oven at 325° until brown.

title: marble pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening, gradually adding sugar. Continue to beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, creaming well after each.
Blend in vanilla.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook together squash and onion.
Mash until soft.
Add sour cream and soup.
Add melted butter to stuffing and mix in a separate bowl.
Put half of stuffing in casserole.
Pour in the filling.
Cover with the rest of stuffing.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
This freezes well.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Roll biscuits very thin.
Place some chicken on each biscuit. Fold biscuit over and press edges together with a fork.
Fry in 350° oil for 10 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal bars
directions: Cream together the butter, egg, sugar and bananas.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Oil and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: ham delights
directions: Slice top of rolls.
In a saucepan, heat butter, onion flakes, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Cook on stove a few minutes until butter has melted.
Spread mixture on top and bottom layers of rolls.
Cut ham and cheese to fit rolls.
Alternate 2 slices of ham with 2 slices of Swiss cheese.
Replace tops of rolls.
Place in a baking pan and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and rolls have lightly browned.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind pepper, onion and ham.
Mix all ingredients.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Combine almond bark and peanut butter; stir until mixed well. Add remaining ingredients; mix and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: custard pie
directions: Grease pie plate with butter.
Beat the eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Beat until well mixed. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. This pie makes its own crust.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Place 6 apricots, cut side down.
Cut slits in apricots to within 1/4 inch from one end, forming a fan.
Set aside.
Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of wax paper and flatten.
Combine flour, salt and white pepper; dredge chicken.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat. Cook for 6 minutes, or until brown, turning only once.
Remove from skillet to heated platter.
Add 1 cup apricot liquid, cornstarch, bourbon and lemon juice.
Bring to boil.
Serve with apricot fan sauce and pecans.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine potato flakes, cheese, parsley, onion powder, garlic powder, paprika, and pepper.
Mix well.
Coat chicken pieces in melted margarine and then coat with potato mixture.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours or until golden brown.
May use chicken wingettes in place of larger pieces.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise and sugar together.
Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Top with mayonnaise mixture. Sprinkle with bacon bits and shredded cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Mix all together.
Put into a 5-quart ice cream pail.
Freeze.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Put in refrigerator until it starts to thicken.
Fold in 1 small can mandarin oranges, drained and mashed, and 1/2 pint Cool Whip.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix with taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer above ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with sour cream, if desired.
Serve with any top of corn chips (tostados, Doritos, etc.).

title: honey ham kabobs
directions: Combine brown sugar, honey and orange juice.

Mix well and set aside. Alternate ham cubes, pineapple pieces and olives on skewers. Grill over medium heat 10 to 12 minutes, turning often and basting liberally with the honey mixture after each turn.

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, spoon into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked sauerkraut and spareribs with dumplings
directions: Cut spareribs into serving size portions and place in a roaster.
Cover with sauerkraut (which has been rinsed in cold water) and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: calico beans-hobo beans
directions: Drain all but the pork and beans.
Fry bacon until crisp. Remove from skillet and crumble.
Brown ground beef with the chopped onion, then add bacon.
Drain grease.
Combine beans with ketchup, brown sugar, white sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Add meat mixture and put in casserole.
Bake 1 hour or longer to thicken.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Mix each package of flavored gelatin separately with 1 cup hot water.
Bring milk and sugar to a boil.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup water and add to milk mixture.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Beat with hand mixer until creamy.
Divide filling into thirds.
Into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish set each layer for approximately 30 minutes before adding next.
Alternate gelatin with filling mix.

title: buckeye pie
directions: In a bowl, combine yolks and milk.
In a heavy saucepan, combine cornstarch and brown sugar.
Stir milk mixture into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Strain to remove any lumps.
Stir in peanut butter.
Cover pudding with plastic wrap to prevent a "skin" from forming.
Cool to room temperature; spread in pie shell and cover with topping.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in the order in which they appear in the recipe.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Cool for 15 minutes. Frost with sour cream if desired.
Serve with Tostitos or Doritos.

title: sumi salad
directions: Saute sesame seeds, slivered almonds and oil until brown.

title: lemonade pie(easy summer dessert)
directions: Blend
well
and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Let set in refrigerator an hour or more before cutting.

title: prized rice pudding
directions: In double boiler, put rice, milk and salt.
Cook low enough to see just a slight boil for 1 hour.
Cover with lid for most of the hour.
Important:
Only stir a little every 10 minutes.
Make sure rice is done before you continue.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Mix grated cheese, olives, bell pepper, pecans and mayonnaise.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix well and pour over shrimp that have been cleaned and cooked with crab boil.
Alternate layers of shrimp, onions and bay leaves in a glass dish that can be securely covered.
Be sure that each layer of shrimp is covered with onions and that all of shrimp are fully covered when finished.
After you secure cover over dish, store in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
This mixture will keep from 7 to 10 days.

title: orange slice nutty fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Put flour in large bowl and add chopped dates, nuts, coconut and orange slices.
Stir to coat each piece.
Add flour and fruit mixture to creamed mixture.
Dough should stiffen (you can handle with hands).
Put into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in a 250° oven 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: shanghai beef
directions: Put oil in pan, add steak strips.
Brown.
When steak is fully browned, add cornstarch to pan.
Mix until cornstarch has soaked up all juices.
Add beef broth, green and red pepper strips, bean sprouts, soy sauce and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
When boiling, add minute rice.
Remove from heat and cover pan.
Let stand 5 minutes or until rice is fully cooked.
Serve.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all together and chill.
These are the basic ingredients, but you can increase or decrease any or all of them to suit your taste.

title: chicken au vin
directions: Place chicken in baking dish or pan and salt.
Combine remaining ingredients, including the mushroom liquid; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish and pour melted butter over it.
Add a layer of rice and top with both cans of soup.
Add water and a little salt.
Bake in covered dish or cover with foil. Bake at 375 degrees for 1
1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, salt and pepper together.
Roll into 8 to 10 small balls.
Put into baking dish with 1/2 inch water.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare one egg cake batter. Cover the bottom of shallow cake pan with waxed paper. Cover with melted butter, brown sugar and a layer of sliced pineapple. Pour in batter and bake in a moderate oven (375°) 30 minutes.

title: company chicken
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with chipped beef.
Wrap chicken with bacon.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Do not salt or cover.
Bake 300° for 3 hours.
Top with sliced mushrooms last 15 minutes (optional).

title: berry muffins
directions: Wash and dry berries. Chop if large.
Mix flour, sugars, baking powder and salt. Combine liquid ingredients and stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Fold in berries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; drain.
Crumble; set aside. Pour off all but 1 tablespoon bacon drippings; add onion.
Saute until tender.
Blend in cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir reserved liquid into skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in sugar and vinegar.
Add beans; heat until bubbly-hot. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and egg.
Serve hot.

title: polynesian wedding cake
directions: Beat well with electric mixer the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well with a spoon.
Do not use a mixer.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Boil chicken with onion, celery and salt; debone.
Saute onions, garlic and green peppers in butter.
Stir constantly, then add tomato paste and water.
Add chicken; cook about 20 minutes. Keep chicken broth.

title: peach pie
directions: Pour peaches in pan; dot with butter.
Mix flour, milk and sugar, then pour over peaches.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°.
May use any fruit.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve with chopped vegetables or chips.

title: telephone salad
directions: Mix together.
Best if left in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: doris' barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Makes large amount, but will keep a long time.
I always put it back in my empty bottles.

title: "old reliable" shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse cocktail shrimp well.
Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with veggies or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour popcorn and sprinkles and flour into a big bowl.
Mix with a spoon.
Put it in the oven.
Then put butter and cream and popcorn seeds in.
Mix in chocolate and pudding.
Put bananas and strawberries in.
Put in cherries.
Put in oranges and water.
Put in grapes and sugar.
Then put in whipped cream and cook it.
Then cut it and eat it.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in water 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth for 7 to 10 minutes.
Chop onion and green pepper and saute in oleo.
Warm milk, soup, cheese and allow cheese to melt.
Mix deboned chicken, spaghetti, onions, peppers, milk, soup and cheese and pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes uncovered.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown the ground meat and onions.
Drain any liquid.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until flavors are well blended, about 1 hour.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Mix flour, spices and salt in bowl.
Beat eggs slightly, add milk and butter (oleo) to eggs.
Add to dry mixture; add nuts. Pour into partially baked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour in a 300° oven.

title: banana and sour cream mold(diabetic)
directions: Dissolve 1 package of gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup of cold water and chill until thickened.
Stir in banana and spoon into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes.

title: microwave glazed carrots, apples and zucchini
directions: Combine carrots and zucchini in a 1-quart microwave dish; pour in 3 tablespoons water.
Cook covered on High for 3 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender.
Drain; then gently toss apples into the vegetable mixture.
In a small mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and cut in margarine with a fork. Sprinkle mixture over top of apple-vegetable mixture.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Gently toss mixture coating apples and vegetables with the glaze.
Cook uncovered 2 to 3 minutes or until glaze thickens.

title: snappy green beans with basil dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except green beans. Put in small bowl. Place in center of serving platter and surround with green beans.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together and drain. Add rest of ingredients and simmer on low heat for 30 to 40 minutes. This is so delicious and so easy!!!!

title: aunt velva's gumdrop cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and 2 cups flour.
Combine applesauce, raisins, gumdrops, nuts, remaining flour and spices.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Bake in 350°
oven.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook potatoes in skillet with 1/2 teaspoon oil for 10 minutes until tender.
Spread over hamburger.
Mix soup and milk and put over potatoes.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm. Add remaining ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Form a stiff dough.
Add more flour, if needed.
Let rise in warm place until double in size.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: autumn cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and press onto the bottom of a 9 in. spring form pan.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 10 minutes. Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing well @ medium speed with an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, mix well.
Blend in vanilla and pour over crust.
Mix apples, sugar, cinnamon and spread over cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
cool completely before removing rim of pan.
Chill.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain well.
Put meat in crock-pot and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook until ready to serve. Serve over Doritos with lettuce and ripe chopped tomatoes on top.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Cook
sausage
and onion until brown, drain.
Mix other ingredients.
Put
one-half
of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread
sausage
and	onion over this, then cheese.
Add remaining mix and bake at 375° until brown.

title: cheese bites
directions: Beat butter at medium speed until creamy; gradually add cheese.
Combine flour, salt, red pepper; gradually add to cheese mixture, mixing well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer first four ingredients in greased baking pan.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over layered mixture.

title: microwave corn and potato chowder
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Combine bacon and onion in 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on Full powder for 10 to 15 minutes, until bacon is cooked and onion is tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook, covered, on Full power, 15 to 17 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Continue stirring during cooking time.
Add remaining ingredients; cook, covered, on Full power for 5 to 8 minutes.
Do not boil.
Stir halfway through cooking time.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given in a large bowl.
Drop by teaspoons, they spread out.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350° (do not overbake).
They freeze well.
Makes about 156 cookies.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put sugar, butter, syrup and salt in 1-quart glass bowl and cook 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda; stir well.
Spray Pam on inside of paper bag (large, brown).
Pour popcorn in bag.
Pour syrup over popcorn.
Fold top over and cook on High 1 1/2 minutes. Take out; shake well.
Cook again 1 1/2 minutes; shake again. Cook 1/2 minute.
Rip bag open to cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill and serve with fruit.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Place half of crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread butter mixture over crumbs.
Top with cherry filling.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill for several hours.

title: hamburger yum yum casserole
directions: Mix together hamburger, onion, salt, pepper and brown sugar. Brown.
Drain off most of grease.
When lightly browned and drained, add tomato juice, stirring well.

title: peach nut salad
directions: Line a salad bowl with lettuce leaves.
In another bowl, combine celery, walnuts and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add peaches. Spoon on top of lettuce and serve.
Serves 6.

title: chopped steak surprise
directions: Chill Chardonnay.
Do not over-chill!
Most people over-chill their white wines. If you can, pull out of the refrigerator early and let it stand for a few minutes. Open bottle carefully.
Most white wines do not need to breath, but do yourself a favor - let it stand a little while.
Disregard the above on Friday nights - any temperature is okay.
Just open the stuff!

title: art and betty's deli meat loaf
directions: *Note:
When we made this recipe at the deli, there was always discussion about whether to use dry or moist bread crumbs.
We never did settle the disagreement.
We made the meat loaf both ways many times and it always tasted good.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together peanut butter and margarine.
Add vanilla. Slowly add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Dough can then be shaped into small balls.
Refrigerate balls until you are ready to coat.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Keep chocolate warm while dipping. Use toothpicks or fork to dip and place on wax paper.
Chill until set.
Makes about 60 or more pieces.

title: almost better than anything cake
directions: Bake according to directions on box. Punch holes in top of cake as soon as it comes out of oven.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over top of cake.
Pour caramel sauce over the top of cake. Let set for at least 1 to 2 hours so cake can absorb milk and caramel sauce.
When cake is cool, spread
Cool Whip over top. Decorate with chopped cherries and nuts.

title: saffron rice
directions: In a heavy 10 to 12 inch skillet, heat the oil over moderate heat until a light haze forms above it.
Add the onions and, stirring frequently, cook for 5 minutes or until they are soft and transparent but not brown.
Pour in the rice and stir for 2 to 3 minutes to coat the grains well with oil.
Do not brown the rice. Add the water, salt and saffron and bring to a boil, still stirring.
Cover the pan tightly and reduce heat to its lowest point.
Simmer undisturbed for 20 minutes or until all liquid has been absorbed by the rice.
Fluff rice with fork before serving. If rice must wait, cover with towel and keep in a preheated 200° oven.

title: braided easter bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Add very warm water and butter; blend well.
Stir in 3 eggs, 1 egg yolk (reserve egg white) and enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cover; let rest on floured surface 10 minutes.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thickened. Take from heat and add jello. Mix in sweetened fruit. Layer angel food cake with sweetened fruit mixture, ending with fruit on top. Can put Cool Whip on top layer.

title: portuguese soup
directions: In a large pot, put the first 8 ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients and boil for an additional 3 minutes.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time (thoroughly mixing one egg before adding another).
Add flour slowly.
Add whipping cream and flavoring.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: virginia's pineapple pie
directions: Heat pineapple and margarine until margarine is melted.
Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and margarine to egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch) and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: "Once upon a time,
there were four people; their names were Everybody, Somebody,
Nobody and Anybody.
Whenever there was an important job to
be
done,
Everybody
was
sure
that Somebody would do it.
Anybody
could have done it, but Nobody did it."

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and flavorings.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour and measure. Sift flour with soda.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill dough.
Scoop 1 1/2 tablespoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 100 cookies.
Eat and enjoy.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in mustard and ketchup; mix well.
Blend in cream of celery soup.
Stir in Veg-All.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve over toasted hamburger buns, open faced.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain everything except pineapple.
Use pineapple juice in pudding in place of milk.
Cook as usual.
Arrange fruit in bowl; pour pudding (as soon as done cooking) over fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: spicy cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cheese, both Cheddar and cream cheese, mixing well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well and chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll ball in nuts.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: golda young's chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick 1 1/4 cups sugar, cocoa, flour, salt, well beaten egg yolks and the milk.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Cool. Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry.
Beat the egg whites.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on pie and brown.
In loving memory of Mother.

title: cheese straws
directions: Enough milk to rolling consistency.
Roll as thin as possible.
Cut in 1/2 x 8 strips.
Bake at 425° until light golden brown.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Roux:
Mix flour and oil together in a 4-cup measure. Microwave on High 7 minutes.
Stir well, microwave on High 30 seconds more.
Roux will be dark caramel.

title: potato cream soup-bulgaria(kartofena krem soopa)
directions: Finely cut carrots, onion, parsley and potatoes.
Saut carrots, onions and parsley in 2 Tbsp. of butter.
Put in kettle, add potatoes and cover with water.
Cook over low heat to a boil. When vegetables are well cooked take off heat.
Mash thoroughly and pass through a colander.
Bring milk to a boil.
In a separate kettle, brown flour in 1 Tbsp. of butter.
Slowly pour boiling milk into the flour, stirring all the time.
Add vegetables.
Place all ingredients in a kettle with the vegetable-flour mix.
Double boil the mixture for 10-15 minutes, stir to prevent sticking to bottom. Remove from heat.
Put egg yolks in a bowl, add 2-3 Tbsp. of soup stir vigorously, thinning egg yolks.
Add mixture to soup and stir well.
Serves 8.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil raisins, dates and apples in a scant cup of water for 3 minutes.
Add shortening and cool.
Add eggs, sweetener, vanilla and soda.
Add flour and nuts last.
Mix well.
Chill dough overnight in covered container.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes. If there are leftovers, store in the refrigerator in tightly covered container.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in loaf pan at 325° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix following ingredients together:
ground meat, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into meatballs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
In slow cooker, put chili sauce, cranberries and sauerkraut.
Stir.
Add meatballs and let cook at low temperature, 3 to 4 hours, the longer the better.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, place 1/3 cup of mix in a cup.
Add boiling water and stir well.
Yields 16 cups of mix (48 servings).

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in beans, dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes. Combine lettuce and green onions.
Add meat mixture to lettuce and green onions.
Add cheese and toss lightly.
Sprinkle small amount of cheese to top of mixture.
Serve with crisp tortillas.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan tassies(yields 24)
directions: Mix and divide into 24 balls.
Press into pans and add filling.

title: hamburger pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix soups and tomatoes in a large ovenproof dish.
Brown onions and ground chuck and drain.
Mix with soup mixture and cover with tater tots.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook another 15 minutes to brown.
Serve with cheese if desired.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble bacon, broccoli, raisins and seeds. Stir together mayo, sugar and vinegar; spoon over broccoli mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Add pretzels and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Add whipped topping and mix well.
Spread over pretzel mix cooled.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water and add frozen strawberries.
Stir until strawberries are separated.
Pour over cream mixture and chill until firm.

title: baked rice
directions: Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Stir once after 1/2 hour.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl; roll out dough.
Use cookies cuter to cut dough into different shapes.
Let ornaments dry.
Not edible!
Before dry poke a hole through the dough with a pin to hang.
When dry, paint with shirt paints or other paints to put on features.

title: no-bake stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half, lengthwise.
Remove and discard stems, ends and seeds.
Parboil in boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain.
In a mixing bowl, add sugar and basil to the can of tomato sauce and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion well in a large skillet.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce mixture, 1/4 cup of the rice and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes; stir in cheese.
Spoon meat mixture into peppers and place in skillet.
Pour remaining tomato sauce mixture around peppers.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, bring water, 1 teaspoon salt and the butter to boil.
Stir in remaining rice. Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve peppers over the rice; top with additional sauce and cheese.
Serves 3.

title: cornbread pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet over medium heat, saute garlic in oil for 1 minute.
Add zucchini, bell pepper, onion and carrot.
Cook 10-15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in chili and mix gently.
Spread mixture in a 9 inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions; spread over cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes or until cornbread is golden brown.
Serve with salsa, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Cream the
ingredients	and spread on top and bottom of buns. On the
top piece, put one slice of Swiss cheese and on the bottom piece, put a slice of ham. Bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix above ingredients (without cheese) with one package (mixed per directions) Italian dressing.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix the other package of Italian dressing mix; pour over pasta, then add cheese just before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Use no salt.
Fry hamburger and sausage in skillet until done; drain.
Add onion, garlic, all peppers and spices.
Fry until onion and pepper are soft.
Add tomato paste and juice.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Make spaghetti noodles and mix sauce and spaghetti.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts several hours in sauce.
Bake in marinade for 1 hour at 350°.

title: candied orange peel
directions: With a sharp knife, score peel of oranges into quarters. Remove peel gently with fingers.
Heat orange peel and 6 cups of water to boiling.
Simmer 30 minutes; drain.
Repeat process, cooking peel in another 6 cups water.
With spoon gently scrape off remaining white membrane from peel.
Cut peel lengthwise into 1/4 inch strips.
Heat 2 cups sugar and 1 cup water to boiling, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add peel; simmer 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Turn mixture into strainer; drain thoroughly,
Roll peel in 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Spread on waxed paper to dry.
May use to eat or decorate cakes etc.

title: my grandmother's carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder. In a separate bowl, beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Combine both; mix in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven for the 1 hour of baking.
Test with toothpick.
Cool on rack and sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: In heavy skillet (with metal handle) heat oil.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Add garlic and cook until slightly brown. Stir in tomatoes.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in bowl.
Heat oleo, cocoa and Coke to boiling point; pour over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Batter will be thin and marshmallows will float to top.
Pour batter into oiled and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice cake while still hot.

title: macque choux
directions: Best described in the South as smothered corn.
May be prepared ahead and stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown onion, bell pepper and ground beef together and drain. Add corn and tomatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add corn meal gradually with tomato juice, salt and chili powder.
When this has been mixed thoroughly, remove from fire and add olives.
Pour into 2 medium casseroles.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and bake another 10 minutes.
Tastes better if sets overnight and reheated the following day.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream and pour over grapes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and cook 7 minutes in boiling water.
Drain, cool and remove 12 larger leaves.
Cook meat, onions and peppers in oil until meat is brown.
Add crumbs, chili sauce and seasoning; mix well.
Put an equal amount on each cabbage leaf, roll up and secure with toothpick.
Put in large baking pan, pour in tomato sauce and dot with butter.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove rolls to platter.
Stir sour cream into sauce in skillet and serve with rolls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion in melted margarine.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup.
Beat eggs and add mayonnaise.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oriental saladeverton, missouri
directions: Drain all canned vegetables and mix with fresh vegetables in large serving bowls.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix well and serve with chips.

title: layered lemon cheese cake
directions: In bowl , mix flour and sugar, cut in butter.
Mix well.
Pat dough into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Place sugar, flour and soda in a large mixing bowl and mix together.
Heat in saucepan until melted the cocoa, butter and hot water.
Mix together buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and add to cocoa mixture mixture, then add to flour mixture.
Blend all together; don't beat.
Put in well greased and floured sheet pan, 10 x 15 x 1-inch.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put squash, onion, carrot, salt and water in pan.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Drain in colander and put in bowl.
While vegetables are still hot, add margarine, soup and sour cream.
Mix well and add 1 cup stuffing mix and grated cheese.
Place mixture in a greased 2 or 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with 1/4 cup stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: egg sausage brunch
directions: Combine eggs, salt and mustard. Beat together. Add milk, bread, cheese and sausage. Stir to blend. Pour into 8 x 12 Pyrex baking dish (buttered). Refrigerate overnight.
Place dish in pan of water (1/2 to 1-inch) in preheated 350° oven. Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat.
Now add dry ingredients.
Add sour cream, stirring smooth after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake in hot 400° oven until done.
When cool, spread with icing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients (room temperature) thoroughly.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: turkey puff
directions: Mix soup and 1/3 cup water; put in 2-quart casserole.
Arrange turkey stuffing and beans in layers on soup.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then beat yolks until thick; fold into whites.
Pile on casserole.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with onions.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes longer.
Great with Thanksgiving leftovers!

title: tomato and green pepper salad
directions: Use amounts needed for size of salad.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Pick over, wash, drain and crush the berries.
Measure to make sure you have nine cups.
Add the water.
Boil until berries are soft.
Add the sugar.
Boil to almost
jelling point.
Pour boiling hot into jars and seal at once.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow pan.
Blend soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Combine margarine, cracker crumbs and poppy seeds.
Sprinkle over the top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour, salt and brown sugar; mix well.
Beat egg yolks in a bowl.
Add together with milk and vanilla; cook until tick, stirring gently.
Take off stove and stir 5 more minutes.
Pour into cooked pie crust.

title: curried turkey salad(lo-cal)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Don't leave out the curry powder and sesame seed.
It is good.
Yields 4 servings.
Each serving equals 4 protein, 1 fat, 1 fruit and 10 calories.

title: low-fat vanilla milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: gourmet meatballs
directions: Mix and form into meatballs.
Melt margarine in frying pan. Flour meatballs and fry in margarine.
Pour off excess fat.
Mix mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and water.
Mix in pan to make gravy.
Serve over rice, noodles and mashed potatoes.
Can make and freeze ahead of time.

title: 3 layer dessert
directions: Mix as you would for pie crust.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add salt to chicken and cook.
Remove chicken from broth and debone.
Add 1 stick butter to broth.
Mix corn meal, eggs and milk together.
Makes 2 skillets of bread. Cook about 30 minutes, till brown.
Crumble corn bread and crackers in large pan; add onions, celery, salt and pepper.
Add small amount of broth at a time until you have a cornbread like mixture, taste to see if more salt and pepper is needed.
Save 3 cups mixture and pour remainder into 2 - 9 x 12 casserole dishes. Add chicken pieces and cover chicken pieces with a little of the reserved mixture.
Cook in 350° oven for 40-50 minutes or until browned.
Recipe may be halved.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, combine the sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes (or to 210° on candy thermometer), stirring frequently, scraping bottom of pan.
Add butter and pecans.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, scraping bottom and sides of pan, until candy reaches soft ball stage (234°, about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Drop from tablespoon onto waxed paper and let cool.
Makes about 18 two-inch pralines.

title: himmen und erde(german for heaven and earth)
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes, apples and sugar.
Heat to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Drain.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Cook onion in bacon fat until tender.
Place potatoes and apples in a serving bowl.
Dot with margarine; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Top with onion and bacon.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini salad
directions: Mix vinegars and spices.
Add to vegetables; mix carefully. Marinate in refrigerator at least 6 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pat in bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish, saving some for top.

title: working mother's cake
directions: Combine
dates and boiling water.
Cool.
Stir shortening
to soften,
gradually
add
sugar.
Cream
until fluffy. Blend
in vanilla.
Add
eggs,
one at a time.
Beat well. Sift
together the
cake flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with date mixture.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Sprinkle top with bits and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: wassail
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth.
Boil all ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 40 cups.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then stir in 1 large package of real chocolate chips.
Bake 1 hour in large Bundt pan at 350°.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Mix ingredients, except cherries and wafers, until smooth with beater.
Using cupcake papers, place vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup.
Put in creamed cheese mixture to 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 10 or 15 minutes, until dry.
Turn off oven and leave door open for 1/2 hour.
Remove cupcakes and cool.
When cool, add topping, which is a can of cherry pie mix.
Put 3 cherries on each tart.
Can be frozen.
Thaw out in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 25 tarts.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
boiling water.
Add other ingredients. Put
in a gallon container and finish filling container with water
and	freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw and add 2 quarts ginger ale.

title: chicken pillows
directions: Remove skin from breasts.
Pound lightly to flatten.
Place mushrooms in a frying pan with chives, 1/2 cup wine, celery and seasonings.
Simmer until liquid has evaporated.
Divide mixture into 4 parts and spread on chicken.
Roll up and secure with string.
Fry chicken in oil until golden brown on all sides.
Place in ovenproof casserole.
Add 3/4 cups dry white wine, parsley, water, stock cube, salt and pepper to the frying pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce slightly, then pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in the oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Drain liquid from casserole into a saucepan; return chicken to oven to keep hot.
Boil liquid until reduced by half.
Remove from heat; stir in yogurt.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Garnish with parsley and serve while hot.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine pineapple and Jell-O in a saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring until Jell-O is dissolved.
Boil for 3 minutes, cool completely.
Add buttermilk and nuts; fold in whipped topping.
Pour in dish and refrigerate until set or overnight.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Mix these ingredients and bring mixture to boil for 1 minute. Cool.
Pour over cole slaw.
Freeze in serving size containers. Thaw just until slushy to serve.
Keeps in freezer for about 10 months.

title: cranberry squares
directions: Melt margarine; remove from heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put into an 8 x 10-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate on low heat.
Add sugar and eggs, stirring to blend.
Add flour, vanilla and coconut; do not overmix. Pour into a 9-inch greased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6. To serve, top with a scoop of ice cream.

title: vi's meat loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and press into an 8 x 10-inch rectangle.

title: baked creole cod(low calorie)
directions: Spray a shallow nonstick baking dish with cooking spray; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Arrange the fish in a single layer; sprinkle with remaining lemon juice.
Combine tomatoes, Italian herbs, celery, onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, thyme, garlic, hot pepper flakes, salt and pepper; spoon over fish.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until fish flakes easily and sauce is thick.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving contains 155 calories.

title: low calorie dessert cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake into small pieces, putting 1/2 of cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan and spreading 1/2 of pineapple over it.
Add Cool Whip, then take the other 1/2 of cake crumbs and spread on top of the other cake mixture as you did before: crumbs, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle baked coconut on top of cake and put in refrigerator for best results.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the orange juice, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Pour over chopped fruit.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Chop nuts, mix with chips and sprinkle with some of the dry cake mix or a little flour.
Coat well and set aside.
Mix other ingredients (beat with mixer).
Put about 5 tablespoons plain batter in Bundt pan which has been sprayed with Baker's Joy or greased and floured.
Fold nuts and chips into remaining batter and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand in pan for 15 minutes before turning out.

title: no-knead onion barbecue buns
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm by adding water.
Add yeast, egg and onions.
Add flour, mix to soft dough and shape.
For round buns, roll dough to 1/4-inch thick an cut with 3 1/2-inch cutter.
For square buns, roll dough to 9 x 12-inch rectangular shape.
Cut into 12 (3-inch) squares.
For wiener buns, divide dough into 12 parts, then shape into long, narrow buns.
Place on greased sheet.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Bake 15 minute at 400°.

title: babysitter's surprise
directions: Brown hamburger, cook noodles according to package.
Add soups to hamburger and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: split pea soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in bacon fat.
Cook until soft and put in blender.
Add more seasoning.
With corn bread, this makes a good meal.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Cook all ingredients.
Pour in the two pie shells.

title: quickie chocolate cake
directions: Heat margarine and Dr. Pepper until margarine melts.
Do not boil.
Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and cocoa into mixing bowl.
Combine egg, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Add the hot Dr. Pepper mixture to the dry ingredients and blend well. Lastly add the egg mixture, mixing well.
Pour into a sheet cake pan and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat egg yolks; add to sugar mixture. Add poppy seed.
Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add sour cream alternately with flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°. Invert to cool.

title: brown chicken fricassee
directions: Flour chicken and brown in oil.
Saute celery and onion, then add soup and water.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Cover with other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: market day chuck wagon casserole
directions: Place meatballs, celery, green pepper, onion, tomato sauce and seasonings in a large heavy skillet.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add beans and turn into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place a cube of cheese on each biscuit; fold biscuits in half.
Firmly press edges to seal.
Place on meatball mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are brown and done.
Test with toothpick.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and rinse blueberries.
Pour oil into 8-inch cake pan, tilting pan to cover the bottom.
Put mix, egg and water into pan.
Stir with fork 1 minute.
Sprinkle blueberries, brown sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Use fork to fold into batter just enough to create a marbled effect.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare spinach according to cooking instructions, drain.
Combine stuffing with margarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Spoon 1-inch balls onto lightly greased cookie pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet. Drain grease.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; put in baking pan.
Place chicken on top and bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: tricky torte
directions: Slice pound cake across into 5 to 6 slices while still cold. Melt chocolate bits in double boiler and stir in sour cream.
Ice each layer plus top and sides.
Top with toasted almonds, pressing lightly so they will not fall off when cake is sliced. Refrigerate or freeze.
If you choose to freeze, defrost in refrigerator 24 hours.
Always let stand at room temperature a while before serving.
Easy to make.
Serves 10.
You can pour a little Amaretto Liqueur on each slice, if you wish.

title: one skillet cabbage, noodles and kielbasa
directions: In large skillet, break cabbage into pieces.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until margarine is melted and cabbage starts to cook.
Slice kielbasa into thin pieces.
Add to skillet of cabbage.
Once cabbage and kielbasa have cooked together a few minutes, add package of noodles.
Add approximately 2 cups of water, stirring occasionally, until noodles are done.
May add more water a little at a time until noodles are cooked.

title: choco-nut dainties
directions: Beat 3/4 cup butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to butter mixture, mixing until blended.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.
Shape dough into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch logs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until set.
Remove to wire racks to cool. Combine remaining 1 cup chocolate morsels and remaining 1/4 cup butter in a small heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, until chocolate melts.
Dip ends of cookies into mixture and roll in chopped walnuts.
Place on wax paper until chocolate is firm.
Store in an airtight container.
Freeze up to 6 months, if desired.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with pared fruit of your choice that has been cut into bite-size pieces (about 6 cups).

title: scalloped potato bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Place beef in a casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and seasonings.
Place potatoes on top. Mix milk with soup and pour on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Pierce skins of potatoes with fork.
Arrange potatoes on microwave-safe paper towel in microwave oven.
Cook on full power for 10 to 14 minutes, or until potatoes are done.
Turn potatoes over halfway through cooking time.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 inch pan with Pam.
Cook sausage and onion together, drain, set aside.
Layer bread, sausage and onion mixture, grated cheese. Pour egg mixture over layers.
Be sure to cover all layers completely with egg mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Soak overnight then bake in the morning at 350° for one hour.

title: apricot sauce
directions: Combine brown sugar with cornstarch, salt and cinnamon in a saucepan.
Add apricot nectar, hot water, orange flavoring and grated orange rind.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter and chopped pecans.
Pour over sweet potatoes until covered, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Keep in refrigerator.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and dry well on paper toweling.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter and add brown sugar, cornstarch and curry powder. Mix well.
Spoon over fruit and bake one
hour, uncovered, at 325°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 15 and costs about 55 cents per serving.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 1 egg.
Spread in dusted jelly roll pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed and drain.
Combine Cheez Whiz and soup and heat through.
Mix all ingredients together and top with margarine/bread crumbs mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Form
into
one large or two small balls.
Roll
in 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans until outside is covered.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Pour sugar over sliced apples and let set 15 minutes.
Add eggs to apple and sugar mixture.
Blend oil into mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt, then add slowly to apple mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until brown.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: jon monzetti
directions: Cook the noodles according to directions on package.
Drain. Set aside.
Saute pork and onion until done.
Add the pork mixture, tomato soup and chunks of cream cheese to noodles.
Mix well.
Place in 2 buttered casseroles.
Save enough cream cheese to dot top of casseroles.
Bake at 350° until cheese is slightly brown and mixture is nice and bubbly.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease pan and bake for one hour at 300°.

title: harvest home casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper in frying pan until cooked through.
In saucepan combine beans, corn and butter.
When beef mixture is done, drain and add to beans and corn.
Cook everything on low heat about 1 hour for full flavor.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Slice zucchini and cook until barely tender.
Mix sour cream, margarine, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper in saucepan over low heat until all melted.
Add yolks and chives, then pour over zucchini in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with crumbs and more Parmesan cheese.
Brown 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs to blend.
Add salad oil, sugar and vanilla; beat until thick and foamy.
Stir in coarsely shredded zucchini and drained pineapple.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, soda, baking powder, nutmeg, nuts and raisins.
Stir gently into mixture just until blended.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in slow oven at 325° until set.

title: easy no cook pineapple pie
directions: Mix the Cool Whip, pineapple, and pudding with a blender and put into the pie shell.
Let set about 15 minutes in the freezer. Serve with a smile!
This is a pie that is easy and most diabetics can eat without harm.
God Bless!

title: olivia's applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and apples or applesauce; mix well. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and allspice.
Add to butter mixture, alternately with milk.
Add raisins and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook in a slow oven (300°) until a toothpick inserted comes out clean, approximately 2 hours.
Very good.

title: light brownies (caramel)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grease and flour a large flat pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cut while hot.

title: fred's famous pickled fish snack
directions: Cut fresh fish filets into strips or chunks.
Fill a quart canning jar 3/4 full with fish and add 1 diced onion.
Add salt, sugar and pickling spice and fill the jar with dry white wine or apple cider vinegar.
Shake thoroughly and refrigerate for 4 days. Shake daily.
Ready to eat or serve.

title: seafoam gelatin mold
directions: Drain juice from pans and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling and pour over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and cream until smooth.
Add to gelatin mixture and heat until blended.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in well-drained mashed pears.
Whip cream and fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold and chill until firm. Serves 8 to 10.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: Follow directions on Hamburger Helper box, then add mushrooms and soy sauce for a taste that's different.

title: pizza crust
directions: Oil your pans.
Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Stir in salt and sugar; mix in flour, enough to clean sides of bowl.
Turn out on floured board and knead for a few minutes, until you can handle dough without it sticking to your hands.
Dust dough with flour and roll it out almost to size of the pan, then pat it into shape.
Add toppings and bake at 425° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: alsatian lentil soup
directions: Put lentils in bowl.
Cover with cold water.
Soak for 2 hours.
Drain.
Melt butter in 6-quart soup kettle.
Add ham and toss over low heat 3 minutes.
Add carrots, onion, turnip and celery and stir until vegetables begin to soften, 6 to 8 minutes. Stir in lentils, garlic and stock.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer until lentils are tender, 45 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
If soup is thin, remove 2 cups vegetables and puree in blender and stir back into soup.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over medium heat.
Add peanuts and continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook until peanuts are completely sugared (coated and no syrup).
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet; separate peanuts with a fork.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes, stirring at ten minute intervals.

title: cheesy macaroni and hot dogs
directions: Cook macaroni; drain (2 cups uncooked).
Saute onions in butter.
Stir in flour and salt; blend in evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add cheeses; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in macaroni and hot dog slices.
Place Cheesy Macaroni and Hot Dogs in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute in butter the celery and onion about 10 to 15 minutes. Add the frozen broccoli and saute about 10 additional minutes. Add the milk, cream of chicken soup, rice and Cheez Whiz.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Place in oven about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: diet 30 day cake
directions: In a gallon jug, mix together peaches with juice and 2 1/2 cups of the sugar.
Do not refrigerate.
