Stir once a day for 10 days; on the 10th day, add pineapple and juice and the other 2 1/2 cups of the sugar.
Stir once a day for 10 days.
On the 20th day, add the fruit cocktail with juice and the maraschino cherries (do not add the juice of the cherries).
Stir once a day for 10 days.
On the 30th day, drain juice from fruit.
Mix together 1 cup of the fruit mixture, cake mix, egg whites, applesauce and raisins.
Bake at 325° in a tube pan for 60 to 75 minutes (until done).

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix chicken or turkey with soup, tomato, chilies and tapioca. Line bottom of crock-pot with some broken tortillas.
Repeat layers of tortillas, chicken soup mixture, onion and cheese. Cover and cook for 6 to 8 hours on low setting or on high for 3 hours.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: chicken with lemon and herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix herbs and garlic in a small bowl. Flatten chicken breasts gently with hand against table.
Arrange them on foil; season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle herb and garlic mixture over the chicken breasts.
Slice lemons; arrange 2 or 3 slices over each breast.
Dot with butter; seal the packets. Set on a baking sheet.
Set packets in the middle of the oven; bake for 30 minutes.
Transfer to plates and allow guests to open packets at the table.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with small amount of water until tender.
Drain excess water; mash.
Add and beat in eggs, milk, salt, pepper, sugar and crackers.
Pour into casserole dish; dot with butter, if desired (my mother does, but I don't), and top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until firm and lightly browned.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and keep warm.
Place chicken between two sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap, and flatten to about 1/4-inch thickness, using meat mallet or rolling pin.
Dip chicken in egg, and coat with breadcrumbs. Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, cook 8 minutes on each side or until chicken is fork-tender and no pink remains.
Remove chicken, and drain it on paper towles;
keep warm.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and milk; blend real well.
Return to heat; stir until rolling boil.
Cook 8 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix and cool jello and water.
Add and mix orange sherbet. Refrigerate until mixture begins to thicken, then add oranges and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: jumbles
directions: Rub flour and butter together.
Add sugar and baking powder. Beat eggs and stir in to make a soft dough.
Roll out and cut. Bake in good hot oven until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen. Mother's recipe.

title: fresh stir-fry melange
directions: Stir-fry first 10 ingredients in hot oil in skillet over medium-high heat until peppers are tender-crisp.
Add vinegar and tomatoes.
Cook until heated through.
Yields 6 servings. Has about 130 calories each.

title: chippy dippy squares
directions: Put in Pyrex dish in layers.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Mix chicken with soup, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over first ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chips ahoy cookies
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix the flour and baking soda in a bowl, set aside. Use an electric mixer to mix the sugars and shortening.
When creamy add the vanilla, salt and egg white.
Add the flour 1/2 cup at a time adding a tablespoon of water as needed to mix the flour - don't exceed 4 tablespoons of water.
this will make a firm dough.
Mix in chocolate chips.
As dough gets thicker, you may want to mix by hand and abandon the electric mixer.
Roll into
2 inch balls and press down with the palm of the hand to flatten. Bake 8 - 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Combine rhubarb (cut in 1-inch pieces), sugar and water. Bring to a boil; cover and cook slowly until tender (5 minutes). Makes 2 cups.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, bananas and butter, then add salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well, then add flour.
Mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Put cherries and sugar together in a pan.
Bring to a good boil.
Remove from stove and pour in cherry Jell-O.
Let cool some. Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into Jell-O mold and refrigerate until set.

title: maryland crabcakes
directions: Melt butter until soft by microwave or low heat (do not scorch butter). Mix butter, mayonnaise, mustard, egg, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper in a large mixing bowl.
Blend in crabmeat by tossing with a fork lightly.
Preheat frypan with 1/4 stick butter.
Pat out crabcakes to your own size and place in preheated frypan.
Brown lightly on both sides.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread rolls on an 11 x 17-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, or just until starting to brown.
Cool. Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden
Valley together; spread over cool dough.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables over top. Cover and cool 4 to 5 hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: fresh apple shake
directions: Wash, quarter and core apples.
Set aside.
Pour pineapple juice and lemon juice in electric blender.
Cover and turn on motor.
Add in order the cinnamon candies and vanilla ice cream. Blend until thoroughly mixed.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in container with tight lid and shake well.
Allow to sit several hours.
Wash and tear spinach or lettuce.
Boil eggs until hard, then chop fine.
Fry bacon, drain and chop.
Mix together and add dressing.

title: extra sharp cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Grate cheese and garlic.
Mix cheese and garlic together (by hand) until smooth in consistency.
(Also can be done in food processor.)
Separate in half.
Make 2 rolls or balls, whichever you prefer.
Roll in parsley flakes.
Refrigerate, but remove long enough before serving to spread on a cracker.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add pumpkin and eggs and mix well.
Stir together all the dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into greased and floured small muffin tins. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 60 small muffins.
This recipe also makes two 9 x 5-inch loaves.
Bake these at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak
beans
overnight
in cold water.
In the morning, pick out bad ones.
Drain beans.
In a large pot, put new cold water and the beans.
Bring to boil.
Add 1 teaspoon of soda. Boil up to lip.
Drain and rinse.
Put new cold water (just to cover
all), beans, chopped onion, salt and salt pork in pot. Bring
to
boil. Cover and simmer on medium.
Add 2 teaspoons of mustard and 1 cup of white sugar.
Stir.
Pour into a large bowl.
Stir
and sprinkle
with
paprika.
Bake at 400° until bubbly,
to
5 minutes.
Turn oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours
until
to 1/2-inch juice is left.
Set on counter until thickens.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package; drain.
Stir butter and Parmesan cheese into hot vermicelli.
Add eggs, stirring well. Shape into pie shell.
Bake until set.
Set aside.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all these ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: quick pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cucumbers.
Pour mixture over cucumbers.
Refrigerate.
Mixture will cover all cucumbers with time.
Ready to eat in 1 to 2 days.

title: blueberry cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking powder, salt, butter, milk and eggs.
Blend at low speed until dry ingredients are moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange blueberries on top.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and boil quartered potatoes until fork tender.
Mash or beat potatoes until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, onions, vinegar, 2 egg yolks (hard-cooked), pickles and olives.
Mix well. Put in salad bowl; chill well.
Garnish with slices of hard-cooked egg, olives and parsley.
May be kept overnight in refrigerator. Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn-zucchini bake
directions: Do not pare zucchini; slice about 1-inch thick.
Cook, covered, in a small amount of water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and mash with a fork.
Cook onion in first teaspoon of butter. Combine beaten eggs, zucchini, onions, corn, cheese and salt.
Put in a baking dish.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Place baking dish on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for thirty minutes.
Put in jars and pressure 60 minutes at 10 pounds pressure for quart jars.
Can also be frozen.
Let cool completely before putting in freezer cartons.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, carrots, squash, onions and soup.
Mix together margarine and stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 of mix in casserole dish, then squash mix.
Add rest of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cappuccino frost
directions: Combine milk, Espresso, sweetener, water and ice cubes in blender.
Blend until frothy.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in a large baking dish.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and milk together.
Put cooked potatoes in margarine and pour milk mixture over potatoes.
Cook for 1 hour at 400° or until brown.

title: philadelphia cheese-steak sandwich
directions: Place Cheez Whiz in top of double boiler with butter.
Heat until soft and drippy.
Keep warm over hot water as you prepare steaks.

title: heavenly peach jam
directions: Quarter the oranges and lemons; seed them.
Then grind fruit quarters (peel and all) in food chopper.
Cut up cherries by hand. Add fruit to cut-up peaches; add sugar and let stand overnight.

title: raspberry rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar in Dutch oven.
Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add berries.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in jello until dissolved.
Pour in hot jars or freezer containers.
Cover and cool.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: applesauce
directions: *Using a sweet variety eating apple may lesson the need for adding sugar.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop small amounts onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes, until lightly brown.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Mix together in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 to 2 hours, or until cooked through.

title: mount vernon cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add the egg yolks, well beaten, then the cream and flour with spices alternately, then the well beaten egg whites.
Last of all, the well floured fruit.
Bake about 2 hours.
Cover top first hour with buttered paper.
This was probably baked in a brick oven at Mount Vernon.
Have fun improvising.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust; cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes more.

title: bush's best all-american chili
directions: In large pan cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Drain excess grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish with cheese.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Beat together eggs and oil.
Add cake mix; beat again.
Add oranges and juice.
Bake at 350° in 3 (8 or 9-inch) round cake pans for 3 thin layers for approximately 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Bring peas to a boil and drain.
Mix carrots with peas.
Layer ingredients as listed.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Pour over top of salad and spread out to seal well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: punch bowl trifle
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions, using a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Cool completely.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add vanilla and pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or whipped topping.

title: french quarter green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan.
Add soup and cream cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cream cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in green beans, onion flakes, salt, pepper and cheese. Spoon mixture into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with almonds, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead and kept in refrigerator until baking.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix in order given.
Cook until done.

title: beef-barley soup
directions: Brown the beef in oil.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 1/2 hours until tender.

title: miniature ham and cheese rolls
directions: Do not break rolls apart, but slice lengthwise through the center layer.
Place ham and cheese between layers.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rolls.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes at 350°.
Rolls can be frozen.

title: breakfast kuchen
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat in the flour, baking powder and extracts.
Mix well.
Reserve 1 cup of this batter.
Spread the remaining batter into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
With a tablespoon, drop the pie filling over the batter.
Then with the cup of reserved batter, dot it over the filling at random.
Don't spread it.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until it tests done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.

title: ground turkey curry
directions: Chop round onion and celery into fine pieces.
Cut carrots and potatoes into bite sized pieces.
In a pot, add ground turkey, round onion and celery.
Completely cover with water and simmer. (Do not add oil.)
After onion and celery are clear, add carrots and potatoes.
Keep on medium/high heat for 15 minutes.
Add in bon curry sauce mix.
Add in 2 cups of water.
Continue on medium/high for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and 7-Up;
chill.
Then mix marshmallows, pineapple and bananas with Jell-O mixture.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half and sugar until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: quick whole wheat pizza dough(a pizza dough that requires no rising.)
directions: Prepare all topping ingredients.
Preheat oven to 475°.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix together lightly.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tofuburgers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: sausage and pepper
directions: In hot skillet, add a little olive oil. Slice hot links to bite size (you can use one or more hot links). Add to hot skillet. Patty out Italian sausage and add to skillet. Cook until done. Remove from skillet, then add garlic. Saute. Now add tomato sauce, sliced peppers and if you want onions. Cook until almost tender, then add back all sausage. Let simmer until all flavors mingle.

title: ham loaf balls
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil and simmer a few minutes.
(Double if making as appetizer.)
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Baste a couple of times and turn after 30 minutes.

title: country pie
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pat meat mixture into bottom and around edges of a 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: trappers breakfast
directions: In
an	8-inch	skillet
heat
bacon
drippings,
break biscuits into
crumbs and stir into drippings.
Add the 2 eggs and scramble with bread crumbs.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add leftovers.	This is an ideal recipe for getting rid of any leftovers at the end of a trip.

title: pull-apart sticky buns
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Combine the pecans, sugar and cinnamon in a medium bowl and mix well.
Unroll the breadstick dough and separate into 8 strips.
Dip each strip in the butter and coat with the pecan mixture.
Starting at the center of a round shallow 2-quart baking dish, loosely arrange the strips in a spiral fashion to form a circle.
Sprinkle with any remaining pecan mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in the dish for 5 minutes.
Invert onto a serving platter.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 sticky buns.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine sugars and wet ingredients.
Beat well.
Add flour and dry ingredients; mix.
Shape in 1 inch balls.
Roll in additional sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Immediately press chocolate candy into cookie.

title: grandmother rachel's 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening; add dry ingredients.
Stir well and bake
in a tube pan until done, about 50 minutes, at 350°.

title: butter pecan cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar, butter and pecans.
Reserve 1/3 cup of the mixture.
Firmly press remaining mixture into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream and flavoring.
Mix well.
Stir in 1 cup pecans.
Spoon into prepared pan on top of crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake for 50 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature on wire rack.
Chill.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Dip chicken in milk, roll in dry ingredient mixture and place in a Pam sprayed pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nutty noodly cluster
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in noodles and nuts so that they are evenly coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and chill.
Yields approximately 24.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening together.
Add sugar gradually, continuing until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours or until carrots and potatoes are soft.
Different vegetables can be substituted according to each family's taste.

title: trail bologna
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll in lengths and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake at 300° for 1 hour. Cool and pat off fat.
Rewrap and refrigerate.

title: cranberry-cheese mold
directions: Dissolve orange-pineapple jello in the boiling water; stir in orange juice. Chill until partially set.

title: fanny mae fudge
directions: Butter bottom of pan to prevent sticking.
Cream together sugar, milk, butter and vanilla in large pot.
Boil for 2 minutes. Turn heat down real low.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted. Add each type of chocolate separately until melted.
Spread onto cookie sheet and cool.

title: spicy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oats, eggs and oil.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas 2
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix.
Put ingredients into flour tortillas, roll up, put in microwave safe dish.
Put 1/2 c. colby cheese on top.
Microwave for 10-12 minutes.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut water chestnuts in half; cut bacon in half.
Roll chestnuts in bacon strip; secure with a toothpick.
Place roll-ups in a square baking pan and bake in a 425° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix cheese, sour cream, sugar salt and marshmallows.
Fold in fruits.
Pour into a freezer-safe container.
Freeze 8 hours. Thaw 10 minutes before slicing and serving over a piece of lettuce.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Prepare instant butterscotch pudding as directed on box.
Add dry yellow cake mix and mix.
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels and chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corny broccoli bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: orange cranberry mold
directions: Mix altogether and let sit in refrigerator.
Mix together 1 small carton sour cream and small marshmallows and cover top when ready to eat.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Combine onion, garlic cloves, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Wash frog legs; pat dry and place in onion mixture for 1 hour.
Mix flour and cornmeal.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove legs from marinade and roll in flour-cornmeal mixture.
Deep fry legs in hot oil at 375°, frying about 4 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with lemon wedge.

title: picnic pastry logs
directions: Place flour in a large bowl; with a pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
With a fork, stir in cottage cheese, blending until dough forms a moist ball.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead for about 1 minute

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
Melt butter. Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add cocoa and melted butter.
Mix in flour; add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together and add remaining ingredients.
Beat on high speed until smooth and creamy.
Set aside.

title: dip for fruits
directions: Beat egg yolks and confectioners sugar for 4 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in egg mixture.
Mix in orange juice.

title: cinnamon applesauce bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Place cooked hamburger in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup and water together.
Pour over hamburger.
Top with 1 package Tater Tots.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serve.
This is a quick main dish.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil for 10 minutes.
Put bread in casserole.
Pour over bread the butter.
Mix, then pour tomato puree over all.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut into chunks.
Mix with soup and sour cream.
Crush Ritz crackers; mix with margarine and poppy seed; spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; you can prepare beforehand and refrigerate, then bake about 45 minutes.

title: pat's brother's perfect biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1/4 cup oil if the humidity is low or 1/3 cup if the humidity is high. Knead a few minutes.
Pinch off biscuit size pieces. Dip in flour to coat. Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Brush butter on top if desired.

title: fudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt 1 cup chips with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour evenly over prepared crust.
Top with nuts and remaining 1 cup chips; press down firmly.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into squares and store tightly covered.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: cheese fingers
directions: Slice bread crosswise into 1-inch fingers, leaving attached. Mix cream cheese and dressing mix. Spread on bread. Pile on toppings. Broil until brown and bubbly. Makes 4 1/2 dozen fingers.

title: chocolate fudge muffins
directions: In saucepan over low heat, combine margarine and chocolate. Melt, stirring frequently, so chocolate doesn't burn or stick.
In a bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in chocolate mixture. Beat eggs, then add them to batter with the vanilla.
Stir until eggs are well blended, but do not beat the mixture.
Line muffin tins with paper liners.
Fill each one about 2/3 full.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Check to see if muffins are done by inserting a toothpick in one near the center of the muffin.
If the toothpick doesn't come out clean, bake for another 5 minutes before removing them from the pan.
These taste much like brownies.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts and apples and stir.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt cake pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Place in a large saucepan.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Cook until tender, about 8 minutes; drain. Combine salad dressing, sour cream, 1/2 c. cheddar cheese and bacon in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and salt; stir well.
Spoon mixture into a medium baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake potatoes until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: missouri beans
directions: Chop bacon; cook with onion and ground beef until brown. Place in casserole and add the rest of the ingredients.
(I drain some of the liquid from the beans so casserole will be thicker when done.)
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sandy duncan's grandma darlin' stew
directions: Brown beef and add to large stew pot.
Add all ingredients at once and cook on a low simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours (or until you can pierce potatoes easily with a fork).
Feel free to add any leftover vegetables from refrigerator such as corn, cauliflower, green beans, okra and broccoli.
Serve with corn bread.
Serves 4.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Will also make enough for a 14 to 18 pound turkey.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening, butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into balls.
Roll in mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Bake about 1 hour in a slow oven (300° to 350°).
Serve with any heated, undiluted mushroom or celery soup for the sauce.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar to creamy.
Add eggs and blend. Combine next 4 ingredients.
Stir alternately with milk into sugar and margarine. Blend in warmed dates (in microwave one minute) and nuts.
Mix all in food processor.
Spread on a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Let cool. Dust with confectioners sugar.
Cut into 24 (3 x 1-inch) bars or smaller.
Cut with pizza cutter.

title: rum cake
directions: Melt butter; add water and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rum.
Drizzle over cake.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake as directed on package for 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine dates, raisins, 1 1/4 cups water, oil, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.	Cook together for five minutes, until mushy. Cool to room temperature.

title: caramel roll topping
directions: Boil all ingredients 1 minute then cool for 5 minutes.
Pour over raised rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let rolls stand for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to package directions.
Cool completely and crumble into a large bowl.
Add corn, onion, pepper, tomatoes, cheese, bacon and eggs.
Mix mayonnaise and salad dressing together in a small bowl.
Combine with other ingredients in the large bowl and refrigerate for about 2 hours.

title: kohlrabi-gemuse(german)
directions: Peel and
slice kohlrabi.
Take green, young leaves off stems and
cook
separately
in
small
pot
with boiling salt water. Drain
this
water.
Set
cooked leaves aside and chop finely. Cook sliced kohlrabi in salt water for a few minutes. Do not overcook.
In
Crisco,
brown
onion and parsley;
add flour. Brown
slightly;
add
kohlrabi water or beef broth or just plain water to make a sauce.
Add bouillon cube, stirring constantly over low
heat.
If
needed, add salt and pepper to taste.	Add kohlrabi
slices.
Carefully
stir	so
as not to break up slices. Let
come	to
a low boil for only a minute. Serve with beef steak and fried potatoes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut steaks into 1-inch cubes.
Brown meat slowly in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole, which has a tight fitting cover.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes. Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: hamburger mush
directions: Brown ground beef until done; drain.
Put in large saucepan and add soup.
Add water as instructed on soup can.
Mix well and cook until hot.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients and freeze.
Thaw to use and add 2 quarts of ginger ale.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Saute butter, onion and bell pepper.
Add uncooked rice, mushrooms and beef consomme.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: celebration punch
directions: Put ice cubes in punch bowl.
Combine all ingredients.
Garnish with pineapple and lime slices.

title: bread crust apple cake
directions: Butter a round cake or pie plate.
Break bread into small pieces and put in pan.
Add milk and let bread soak a little.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla and stir lightly together.
Pare and core the apples and cut as for cake.
Place on top of bread mixture. Use 4 tablespoons of butter and dot top of cake.
Sprinkle with fine bread crumbs and cinnamon or nutmeg as preferred.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Apples should be brown and tender when done.

title: play dough
directions: In saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from heat; put on table and knead slightly.
Store in airtight container.
Will keep several weeks.
Great for Sunday School.
Won't hurt kids if they eat it.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in freezer until slushy. Take out and shake occasionally to make juices throughout.

title: peachy pork chops
directions: Marinate 4 to 6 pork chops (1-inch thick) overnight in this sauce.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender, about 20 minutes. Put into casserole.
Mix cheese, soup and milk well.
Add beaten sauce to the cabbage.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tomato and orzo aspic
directions: Chill 6-cup ring mold in refrigerator.
If cooked pasta and chopped tomatoes are not chilled, chill them in refrigerator also.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Saute seasonings in butter (onions, celery, bell pepper, 3 to 4 pods garlic).
Add shrimp or crawfish and cook until tender.
In a separate pot, over low heat, melt cream cheese, Velveeta cheeses and half and half.
Do not let stick.
Do not boil.
Combine seasoning and cheese.
Serve over fettucini.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blanch broccoli and salt to taste.
Melt cheese in milk; set aside.
Cook rice.
Melt butter and add crushed crackers.
Lay broccoli spears in long casserole dish.
Spoon cooked rice in between spears.
Pour on cheese sauce.
Sprinkle cracker mixture on top. Bake at 350° until bubbles on top (approximately 30 minutes).

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Combine crumbs and Parmesan in shallow plate. Fork-whip egg and oil in shallow bowl.
Dip each piece of chicken in egg, then crumbs.
Arrange in single layer on baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until no longer pink.
Top with Mozzarella and return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings, about 275 calories each.

title: soda crackers
directions: Combine flour, salt and soda.
Stir in milk.
Round dough into a ball and knead a few strokes.
Divide into several pieces and roll out very thin on a floured board.
Lay sheets of dough on ungreased, flat baking sheets.
Sprinkle with salt and prick with fork.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch squares or party shapes with sharp knife. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Easy and fun for children.

title: haystack candy
directions: Slightly
melt	butterscotch chips in saucepan.
Mix in other ingredients.
Spoon onto aluminum foil.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well together. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes. Bakes great in iron frying pan.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a very large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; then gradually add buttermilk and flour, stirring until smooth.
Add water and soda.
By hand, add bran flakes
and All-Bran.
Batter will refrigerate for up to 6 weeks, if you want to bake a few each day.
Bake in 1/2 full muffin tins at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: pina colada
directions: Blend.
Put in freezer to chill and just before serving, blend again.

title: roast beef in foil
directions: Lay a large sheet of aluminum foil in (and across) a baking pan.
Grease the center of the foil and place the beef on the greased spot.
Sprinkle the meat with pepper.
Cover the roast with the cream of mushroom soup.
Then sprinkle the entire contents of the envelope of onion soup over the meat and the mushroom soup.
Form an airtight envelope of foil around the meat. (Use the "drug store" double fold to join the sides and ends.) Fits loose.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes per pound.

title: mount rainier bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter together.
Add eggs, powdered sugar, salt, vanilla, nuts and mix thoroughly.
Cool slightly.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook 1 cup rice with 2 cups water.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Fry bacon crisp.
Push to one side of frying pan.
Brown onion in bacon grease.
Push to side of pan.
Scramble egg(s) in bacon grease.
Add cooked rice.
Add enough soy sauce until colored as desired.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: punch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together the night before.
Add the vodka and then the ginger ale when ready to serve.
I use the bag of frozen fruit instead of an ice ring to keep it cold.

title: velvety cocoa cream pie
directions: Scald the milk in the top of a double boiler.
Mix the dry ingredients together and add to the scalded milk.
Stir until blended and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture begins to thicken.
Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter or margarine and vanilla, stirring until the butter is melted.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Chill pie thoroughly, at least 2 hours.
Serve topped with sweetened whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage, chop with fork and drain. Melt cheese over low heat in a double boiler. After cheese melts add the soup, RoTel tomatoes and sausage and mix well. Cook until well heated.

title: pa dutch lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles until soft and then drain.
Brown hamburger with dried onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Add pizza sauce and ketchup; simmer.
Grate cheeses together.
Layer hamburger, cheese, noodles and cheese four times.
Sprinkle top with grated Parmesan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(Use 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with aluminum foil.)

title: sausage balls
directions: Break up sausage.
Mix with grated cheese and Bisquick.
Spoon out in balls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and zucchini. Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed. Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan. Turn out onto wire rack.
Let cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: *I use low-fat, low salt Ricotta and lite Mozzarella cheeses. The original recipe also calls for 1/2 cup grated Romano or Parmesan cheese which I omit because of the fat content.

title: fancy sliced tomatoes
directions: Put a layer of sliced tomatoes in a shallow bowl about 8 to 10 inches in diameter.
Put a layer of sliced onions on top. Sprinkle a bit of salt and pepper around, a pinch of basil, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon each of vinegar and olive oil.
Add another layer of tomatoes and onion slices.
Repeat the seasonings.
May repeat the layers until bowl is full.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: *May substitute 1/4 cup pepper cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: no fail meringue for pie
directions: (Use at least 2 egg whites or save egg whites from the pie and use that amount.)

title: jalapeno pepper cheese ball
directions: In large bowl or electric mixer, combine ingredients.
Beat until smooth; chill.
On waxed paper, shape mixture into 4 logs (4 x 1 1/2-inch); roll in parsley or pecans.
Serve with crackers. Makes 60 appetizer servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix well the coconut and pecans and spread in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan that has been greased or sprayed with Pam.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box. Spread over coconut/pecan mixture.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Pour or spoon over cake mix. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30-45 minutes. Cake may spill over sides of pan while baking.
This cake is not pretty, but it makes up for looks in the taste.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump in order given into a 9x13 ungreased pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Cut butter in small slices and spread on top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: dietetic cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press each slightly.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Three small cookies contain 24 calories.

title: blueberries in the snow
directions: Break angel food
cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream sugar with cream cheese.
Gradually add milk.	Beat with spoon until smooth. Add almond, vanilla and Cool Whip.	Mix until blended and pour over
cake.
Top with pie filling.	Chill at least 24 hours.

title: garden green beans with bacon
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, place beans and bacon.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to a full boil.

Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until beans are crisply tender (20 to 25 minutes). Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Prepare pie shell as directed.
In a medium bowl, mix coconut pie filling as directed.
Add 1/2 cup of coconut in the pie filling.
After filling is poured into the pie shell, add the other 1/2 cup of coconut on the top of pie and toast in oven, being sure not to burn the coconut.
Let chill for 1 hour and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini into small pieces and lightly cook and drain. Mix dressing and butter.
Mix all ingredients with 1/2 of dressing mixture.
Put in casserole dish and top with remaining dressing. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Combine oil, vanilla and eggs.
Mix in nuts, raisins and apple mixture.
Combine dry ingredients, then add them to moist ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: party cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs.
Mix well, then add vanilla, soda, salt and flour.
Mix well. Can add chocolate chips and walnuts or M&M's (plain or peanut).
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight in hot water.
Drain; put in pot and cover with water.
Add onions and ham bone.
Cook until peas are tender. Remove bone; mash peas real good.
Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend in pea mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: butter icing
directions: Cream butter until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar gradually, then the egg and vanilla.
You can add food coloring if desired. Beat until creamy.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions, peppers and celery.
Add sugar, salt and spices to vinegar and mix thoroughly.
Cook ground mixture in vinegar solution from 5 to 10 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: sweet potato casserole(in honor of lady posey)
directions: Lightly grease the bottoms and sides of a glass 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with butter or margarine.
It is important that only "lightly" greased.
Spoon well mixed mixture into the baking dish and prepare topping.

title: wedding day punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Heat to boiling; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add Kool-Aid to mixture while hot. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients along with water and ice to make 3 gallons.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Simmer together 2 minutes and serve hot.

title: black bean chicken
directions: Put in crock-pot on medium heat. Cook for 4 hours.

title: strawberry easy
directions: Break cake into dish.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream until smooth.
Pour over cake.
Do not stir.
Mix jello in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, freeze until thickens.
Pour over cake and pudding.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cherry streusel
directions: Combine cherries and 1/2 cup sugar in an 8-inch square baking pan, stirring well.
Combine egg white, milk and vanilla, stirring well to blend.
Pour over cherries.
Combine flour and brown sugar in a small bowl, stirring well to mix.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in nuts. Sprinkle crumb mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: turkey-vegetable chili
directions: Warm 2 teaspoons oil until hot, but not smoking.
Add the turkey and brown.
Put turkey aside and drain.
Add remaining 2 teaspoons oil to pan and saute onions and bell pepper until golden (3 to 5 minutes).
Stir in chili powder, garlic and cumin.
Cook, stirring, for 1/2 to 1 minute.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Add turkey and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the kidney beans and corn.
Cook about 5 minutes until last ingredients are heated through.
Serves 4.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 2 cups boiling water in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Stir in pie filling.
Chill until partially set.

title: meatballs in sour cream sauce
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, cheese, milk, onion powder and garlic salt.
Form into small meatballs.
Brown in oil. Drain.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Mix gravy and sour cream and pour over meatballs. Heat; do not boil.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 5 minutes at 425°, then bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: holy thursday apple bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix the yeast with 1/2 cup of the water and a pinch of brown sugar in a large bowl and set aside about 5 minutes.
After 5 minutes, stir in the remaining water, the milk, the remaining brown sugar, the salt and 2 tablespoons of the oil.
Gradually stir in 4 cups of the flour.
Mix, then beat in a mixer or a food processor until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Mix in whole wheat flour, raisins and apple.
Add another cup of flour to make a soft dough.
By hand or with mixer knead dough for 8 minutes, adding additional flour to make a dough that is soft, smooth and not sticky.
Lightly oil a bowl with 1/2 tablespoon of the oil and place dough in it, turning the dough to coat it completely.
Cover and allow to rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: dressing for cole slaw
directions: Mix all together and toss over cabbage.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix together cinnamon and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Cream butter; add 1 c. sugar and egg.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture. Chill a
few hours.
Roll very thin.
Cut with cookie cutters. Put on cookie sheet.
Brush with water; sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Press a piece of walnut in center.
Bake in 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes until light brown.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: the best chili in texas
directions: Brown sirloin and onion in 2 tablespoons olive oil. Add beans, tomatoes and bouillon.
Simmer 45 minutes or until desired thickness.

title: light yeast rolls
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and salt.
Mix. Warm milk.
Add yeast and add to butter mixture.
Add 1 cup flour, set in warm place (cover with towel) and let raise until spongy.
Add 3 beaten eggs and rest of flour.
Let double in size.
Knead dough.
Divide in 3 parts (each will make a dozen rolls).
Let rise.
Roll into a circle and cut in 12 pieces.
Roll from big end to small (crescent shape).
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: great american potato salad
directions: Combine last 9 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add to potatoes and mix lightly.
Chill.

title: danish pastry
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in milk, egg, sugar and salt.
Stir in 3 3/4 cups flour to make soft dough.
Beat dough vigorously about 2 minutes or until elastic.
Sprinkle pastry cloth with 2/3 of remaining flour.
Turn out dough; form or flat ball and sprinkle with remaining flour.
Roll out to an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Slice very cold butter into thin strips lengthwise over 2/3 of dough to form a 12-inch square.
Fold, brushing off excess flour each time this way.
Fold unbuttered third over middle third, then opposite end over top.
Now fold into thirds crosswise, making a 6 x 4-inch block.
It will be 9 layers thick.
Repeat rolling and folding as preceding 3 more times.
I then roll the dough to an 18 x 12-inch rectangle, then cut strips the longway.
Twist the strips and coil into a roll.
Place these on a cookie sheet and let rise in a warm place.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in milk, orange juice and egg. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine with creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: geranium pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in the vanilla. Line a well-greased 10-inch tube pan with the geranium leaves, if desired.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely.
Sift powdered sugar over top of cake if desired.
Yield:
one 10-inch cake.

title: barbecued chicken(microwave)
directions: Place chicken pieces with thick edges toward outside of a microwave dish.

Combine remaining ingredients. Brush half of the barbecue mixture over the chicken. Cover with waxed paper and cook on High for 10 minutes. Brush with remaining barbecue mixture. Cover and cook on High for 10 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cooked white icing
directions: Cook flour and milk on low together until it makes a paste. Let it cool, then add shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat together until light and fluffy.
Spread over a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together; store in closed container.
To use:
Add 2 spoonfuls of mixture to one cup of hot water.

title: scalloped potatoes, easy and very good
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Drizzle butter over flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until browned and bubbly.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill in refrigerator 2 hours or more. Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutter dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken casserole(6 servings)
directions: Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes until heated.
Don't overbake.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour pie filling on bottom of sheet cake pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch. Sprinkle cake mix on top. (Do not mix.) Spoon on melted margarine. Add coconut and nuts. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: curry chicken
directions: Lightly coat the chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in large skillet and lightly brown chicken. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, peanuts, Karo syrup, water and salt.
Cook on medium heat, stirring continuously until peanuts are very brown, to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat; add soda and stir.
Pour on a well buttered baking sheet.
Spread as thin as possible. Serves 15 to 20.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to directions; rinse and drain.
Chop cucumber, tomatoes, onion, celery and eggs.
Mix with linguine. Stir in Italian dressing, McCormick Salad Supreme and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with garlic salt to taste.
Refrigerate for at least 7 hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: miracle salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend well.

title: preacher's omelet
directions: Fry bacon; brown onion and potatoes. Beat eggs and pour into skillet over bacon, potatoes and onions.
When one side is done, sprinkle with cheese.
Fold and cook until set.
Makes 2 servings.

title: yummy sheet cake
directions: Beat oil, eggs and buttermilk well. Add sugar, cocoa, salt, flour and soda. Beat well. Add water and vanilla.
Pour into greased 11 x 17-inch sheet pan. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add milk, sugar, cocoa and salt; bring to a boil for 1 minute, or until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper; let set until cool.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute onion in hot bacon drippings until golden.
Add beef, salt and pepper; brown lightly.
Add beans and soup.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with well seasoned whipped potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese the last 5 minutes.

title: apricot-honey sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat through.
Serve with chicken nuggets or fried chicken.

title: grammy's famous easter eggs!
directions: Mix by hand; form into eggs.

title: cindy's banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fettucine-primavera
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, cook broccoli, zucchini, green pepper, onion and basil in margarine until crisp-tender.
Stir in tomatoes and mushrooms.
Toss vegetable mixture with hot fettucine on serving dish and sprinkle with grated Parmesan to taste.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream together.
Ice cake and sprinkle coconut on top.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and mix with pudding.
Then add pineapple, marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts and mix well.
This fills a large bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together the Crisco, margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs. Mix together other ingredients except cinnamon and sugar.
Slowly add this mixture to the first mixture.
Mix in a small bowl the cinnamon and sugar to taste.
Roll cookies into small balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Slightly flatten onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: far east crab cakes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well. Shape crabmeat mixture into 8 patties.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add crabmeat patties and cook 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned on both sides, turning once.
Transfer to a serving platter.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Place bread crumbs, cheese, mustard, paprika and pepper in large plastic bag.
Shake to blend well.
Brush chicken on all sides with real mayonnaise.
Add one piece at a time to crumb mixture; shake to coat well.
Arrange on rack in broiler pan so that pieces do not touch.
Bake in 425° oven until golden brown and chicken is tender.

title: new years good luck bean soup
directions: Wash beans and cover with water.
Add 2 tablespoons salt and soak overnight.
Drain and add 2 quarts water, ham and onion. Boil slowly 2 to 3 hours.
Add tomatoes, garlic, juice of lemon, salt and pepper to taste and hot red pepper (optional).
Simmer another hour or so.
I served this on New Year's day with cornbread.
Serves a whole bunch.

title: fresh coconut pie
directions: Mix coconut juice and all the ingredients together.
Put on stove and let come to a boil.
Let it thicken.
Put your pie mixture in cooked crust.
Spread icing over mixture.
Put in oven and let brown.

title: roasted honey pepper pork
directions: Score roast 1/2-inch deep completely around roast without cutting string.
Combine all remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon or brush 2/3 of honey mixture over pork to coat.
Place meat on roasting rack in baking pan.
Roast at 325° for hour.
Brush with remaining honey mixture and cook 30 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Blend and fold cheese, butter, sour cream, chives, salt and pepper into potatoes.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat in hot fat in Mirro-Matic. Add other ingredients and stir, except for the last 2 ingredients. Cover; set control at 15 and cook for 5 minutes after control jiggles. Reduce pressure instantly. For a heavier consistency, this mixture may be thickened by cooking, uncovered, with mixture of flour and water, stirring constantly. Quantity of ingredients: 2 1/2 to 4 quarts. Serves 4.

title: guacamole dip(avocado dip)
directions: Mash avocados with fork (not too smooth). Add tomato; mash into avocado. Add chopped onions, can of salsa jalapeno and salt to taste. Squeeze lemon wedge into dip. Mix and serve.
(Avoid making dip too far ahead of time, as it will darken on standing.)

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Mix rest of ingredients.
Place on top of potato mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture and alternate with milk.
Add blueberries, mixing by hand.
Place mixture in muffin tins (2/3 full).
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut vegetables and cover with water.
Boil for 10 minutes. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: brownies a la schulte
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together; add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix well, then pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Crumble beef in a 3-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave 4 to 5 minutes until beef is no longer pink.
Stir 1/2 way through.
Mix in spaghetti sauce, water, macaroni and mushrooms.
Cook in microwave, covered, for 14 minutes.
Stir 1/2 way through. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and let stand, covered, 5 to 6 minutes.
(Microwaves vary and so may cooking times.)

title: peach marmalade
directions: Cook 45 minutes, slowly.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Saute onion, garlic and bell peppers in margarine. After well sauteed, add flour, green chili peppers, half and half and Velveeta and let dissolve. Add crawfish; simmer until done. Cook egg noodles until well done and drain. In a large Dutch oven layer noodles and then crawfish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until cheese begins to turn up at edges. Serve with crackers and green salad. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: frank kabobs(camping ideas)
directions: You also need kabob skewers.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients with enough Miracle Whip to hold together.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: squirrel or rabbit with parsley dumplings
directions: Brown mushrooms in margarine in skillet.
Remove and set aside mushrooms until later.
Brown rabbit.
Add onion, salt, pepper, pickle juice and water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.

title: goldie's pineapple juice dressing
directions: In a saucepan on medium heat bring juices to high simmer. Meanwhile, beat sugar, eggs and cornstarch; add mixture to simmering juices.
Remove from heat and chill.
Fold whipped cream into dressing and pour over fruit salad.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients well drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: devonshire cream(dip for fresh fruit)
directions: In a small bowl with rubber spatula, gradually blend heavy cream into softened cream cheese. Blend in confectioners sugar and refrigerate.

title: rice pizza
directions: Mix together and press into pizza pan or 2 pie pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Top with favorite pizza topping as with any regular pizza sauce, meats and cheese, etc.
Bake 10 minutes, longer.

title: prince of wales cake
directions: Put 1 cup of flour with raisins.
My mother's old recipe.

title: california mix casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients and warm until cheese melts.
Combine with vegetables and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: noodle and sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage and drain.
In 2-quart baking dish mix sausage, sauce, noodles and 1 1/2 packages of Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hulupkies(cabbage rolls)
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
In a large bowl, combine beef, rice, egg, oregano, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup Ragu.
In a large kettle, boil cabbage head, removing leaves as they become very tender.
Roll approximately 2 tablespoons of meat mixture in each cabbage leaf.
Place loose edge down into roaster lined with extra cabbage leaves.
Top with water, Ragu and bacon strips.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Check every 45 minutes. Add water if necessary.

title: john pa's hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and add spices and water.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat the egg with 5 tablespoons of water.
Add one more tablespoon, if needed.
Makes 3 pie shells.

title: pumpkin pies(2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs hard, then add sugar, flour, salt, spices and pumpkin.
Heat milk (part canned milk) and fold in mixture.
Divide into 2 unbaked shells and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° in hot oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: popcorn snack
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, sorghum and salt in 8-cup microwave bowl and microwave at Full power for 2 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave for 3 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir well and pour over popped corn and peanuts in a paper grocery bag. Shake well.
Microwave on Full power 1 minute. Shake bag and microwave one minute.
Shake bag and microwave one more minute.
Shake bag and microwave 30 seconds.
Shake and microwave 30 seconds more.
Pour on cookie sheets to cool.
Store in airtight tins.

title: raisin bran coffee cake(lo-cal)
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt and add cereal and raisins.
Mix well and combine remaining ingredients and add flour mixture, stirring until blended.
Pour in a 9 x 13 x 3-inch loaf pan or 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 20 servings.

title: four layer pie
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and pecans.
Spread in 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend just until slushy.
Do not overblend.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: almond butter balls
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar until light and fluffy; add flavorings.
Stir in flour and nuts; blend well.
Form dough into tiny balls; place about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar while warm.
Cool on racks.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chicken vegetable soup(low-fat)
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Take out chicken, if desired.
Also take out the bones.
Then put in the two cans of chicken broth. When cool, take off the grease.

title: eggnog
directions: Put all together except nutmeg in blender.
Blend, then pour in glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: spicy tomato soup
directions: Melt butter, add sliced onion and soften, add flour, paprika, tomatoes, herbs, and stock.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Strain.
Add sage and simmer till sage is cooked.
Finally add Port.
Soup is cooked when gelatin-like.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and picante sauce together for bottom layer in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Shredded lettuce for next layer.
Shredded cheese for next layer.
Top with tomatoes. Chill until firm in refrigerator. Serve with chips.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoons into boiling oil.
They will turn themselves.
Cook until brown on both sides.

title: kroll's chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add all ingredients and simmer 6 to 8 hours. Kidney beans and spaghetti may be added later, if desired.

title: cheese-smothered chicken
directions: In skillet, slowly brown chicken in butter, about 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until well done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: decorator icing
directions: Cream together shortening and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar and milk alternately until all sugar is used and enough milk to make a good spreading consistency.
Makes a lot.
Cover with plastic wrap, in a lidded container to store in refrigerator for future use.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Cook raisins in small amount of water until water is gone. Mix applesauce, bananas, egg whites, sweetener and oil.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Blend in with applesauce mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans, mix well.
Pour in tube pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Trim crusts from bread; place slices on a shallow platter. Pour oil over bread; let stand until bread is thoroughly saturated.
Break bread in small pieces with fork.
Combine egg yolks with mustard, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat lightly. Stir in bread and crab meat; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Shape mixture into patties.
sprinkle with paprika; saute in heated butter until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: ice cream amaretto pie
directions: Layer bottom of pan with half of Cool Whip.
Layer ice cream sandwiches.
Poke holes in ice cream with a knife.
Pour amaretto evenly over ice cream.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and press them into Cool Whip.
Put in freezer.
Remove and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: soft gingersnaps
directions: Cream together thoroughly the margarine, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Form into walnut size (or desired size) balls.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes, or until tops are beginning to turn golden.
Do not overbake.

title: tangy potato salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, milk and seafood seasoning.
In large bowl, gently miss dressing into eggs and vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.

title: vanilla ice cream(sugar-free)
directions: Pour into freezer can; add enough milk to fill to full line on freezer can.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Put beef and vegetables into Dutch oven or casserole.
Pour soup and Worcestershire over the mixture.
Cover; bake for 3 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: make-ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in medium skillet; cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Spread bread cubes in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish; top with sausage and cheese. Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dilly dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate 1 hour before serving. May be doubled if larger amount is needed.

title: **banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar with shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add pecans.
Mix soda in buttermilk.
Add with flour and bananas. Bake in loaf or layer pans at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add chopped onion, then milk and egg, beaten together. Drop mixture by small spoonfuls into boiling shortening (400°). When done, the hush puppies will float. Drain them on paper towels.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Blend ingredients and add food coloring.
Chill and serve with strawberries or your favorite fruit.

title: ginger sugar cookies
directions: Add sugar to Crisco and blend.
Add egg and molasses.
Then, add dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mozzarella meat pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender. Add tomato paste, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; mix well. Separate crescent rolls.
Place in 9-inch pie plate, pressing together to form crust.
Fill with meat mixture; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Thank God for dirty dishes, they have a tale to tell.
While other folks go hungry, we're eating well.
With home, health and happiness, we shouldn't want to fuss.
For by this stack of evidence, God's very good to us.

title: southern sweet iced tea
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add tea bags and baking soda.
Remove from heat and cover.
Allow to sit for at least 10 to 15 minutes. Pour into gallon pitcher and add sugar.
Then fill with cold water.
Refrigerate.

title: curried baked cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break cauliflower into flowerets.
In covered large saucepan, over medium heat, in one inch boiling water, cook cauliflower with salt for 10 minutes.
Drain well.

title: macadamia balls
directions: In large bowl, beat together butter and 1/2 cup sugar on medium speed until light and fluffy (about 2 minutes).
Add vanilla and water.
Beat until combined.
On low speed, beat in flour until combined and moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Shape into ball and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Make dough into balls using 1 tablespoon for each ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets about 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly golden.
When cool, dust with remaining powdered sugar.

title: lemon dream dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine or butter and pecans and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cheese dip
directions: Chip and melt cheese.
Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Mix cheese, meat and onion mixture, soup and tomatoes.
Simmer on low heat. Serve warm with corn chips.
Can be refrigerated and reheated for later use.
(Use plain tomatoes for a milder taste.)

title: sauerkraut surprise cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light; blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately in water, beating after each addition. Stir in sauerkraut.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with sour cream chocolate frosting.

title: easter eggs
directions: Add coconut, marshmallow cream, butter, cornstarch and vanilla to cream cheese gradually.
Add enough powdered sugar to hold mixture together.
Form sugar mixture into balls or egg shape. Dip in melted chocolate.
Yields about 50.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: If not using a double boiler, you must stir nonstop.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Mix in all other ingredients except cheese soup.
Tear tortillas in small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with the cheese soup.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in white vinegar.
Then add salad oil, water, salt and pepper.
Mix all vegetables in this liquid.
Let set 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: salmon loaf or timbales
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Place in well-greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or 8-inch square or round pan.
Also can be put in greased baking cups or muffin tins (3/4 full).
Bake at 375°; for mini-loaves, 25 to 30 minutes; for larger loaves, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into baked pie shell. Freeze for 6 hours before serving.

title: poor man's crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Add additional bread crumbs, if needed. Shape into cakes. Roll in bread crumbs. Refrigerate for about 30 minutes.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: chocolate bourbon pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except chocolate bits.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9-inch deep dish pie shell for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Place chocolate bits in bottom of pie shell.
Pour into pie filling.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken.
Saute celery in butter.
Add rice and soups. Mix well.
Put rice mixture in baking dish.
Place chicken parts on top.
Cook at 250° for 2 hours or more, until chicken is tender.

title: german chocolate icing(for cake)
directions: In a saucepan on medium heat, melt butter and sugar. Cook until sugar melts. In a separate bowl, stir milk and egg yolks well. Add milk/egg mixture to the butter/sugar mixture in the saucepan. Continue cooking on medium heat; stirring all the while until icing thickens. Remove from heat; add nuts, coconut, and vanilla. Leftover icing will keep several weeks if sorted in a covered container in the refrigerator.

title: gazpacho
directions: In a blender, puree 1 tomato, 1/2 cucumber, 1/2 onion, 1/4 bell pepper, pimento and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Add remaining tomato juice, oil, pepper, Tabasco and vinegar.
Stir.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Chop remaining tomato, cucumber, onion and bell pepper.
Add before serving.
May be frozen.

title: pastry shell
directions: Place flour, butter and salt in processor bowl and cover unit. Process 5 fast pulses or until butter is the size of small peas. With motor running, pour the water all at once through the central feed.
Turn unit off as soon as the dough begins to gather together and before it forms a ball.
Do not overprocess.
Remove from processor bowl and gather into a ball.
Roll out and place in a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Mix coconut and sugar in bowl.
Add cream, a little at a time; it all needs to stick together.
Roll into small balls and then roll balls in cinnamon.
Little children love to make these for St. Patrick's Day.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil ingredients and pour over small sliced cucumbers.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: lemon stickies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine with hands.
Press onto ungreased pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, eggs and cream cheese and pour over dough mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: drunk hot dogs
directions: Cut up hot dogs.
Cover in water; bring to a boil.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar and bourbon together.
Drain water from hot dogs.
Cover in sauce; heat thoroughly.
Can be made ahead of time and reheated in a crock-pot.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash, dry and seed green and red peppers.
Chop peppers and cabbage finely, and mix together.
Add mustard seed, salt, sugar, and enough cider vinegar to cover.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden grilled ham
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate ham overnight in refrigerator; grill ham.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Make pickling solution of vinegar, pepper and spices and bring to a boil.
Add eggs and bring to a boil again.
Pack into hot sterilized jars and cover completely with pickling solution.
Seal immediately.
Let set for a few days before opening and eating.

title: smoothies
directions: In blender container, place 1 to 1 1/2 cups frozen berries. Break into pieces and drop on top of berries, one entire banana. Pour in juice just to cover fruits.
Blend until smooth (doesn't take long!).
For thicker smoothie, use less juice.

title: chilli beans
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Chop onion and pepper and set aside. Mix beans, browned chuck and Chili-O mix (follow directions on package); pour in oil.
Stir; add pepper.
Cook in crock-pot for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except zucchini.
Blend well, then mix in zucchini.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken, saving broth.
Place chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour mixed vegetables over chicken. Slice boiled eggs over soup.
Mix flour and melted oleo. Add 1 cup broth.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake about 25 minutes at 450°.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: chocolate charlie
directions: In top of double boiler, over boiling water, melt chocolate, milk and butter; remove from heat when melted.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (uncovered).
May garnish with additional grated cheese.

title: "unfried french fries"(from "in the kitchen with rosie")
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals, then slice each oval lengthwise into matchsticks. Coat baking sheet with 3 sprays of Pam.
Combine egg whites with Cajun spice in bowl.
Add potatoes and mix to coat.
Pour potatoes onto prepared baking sheet and spread them out into single layer. Place baking sheet on bottom shelf of oven.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, turning every 6 to 8 minutes to brown evenly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4. Fat:
0.5 gram per serving, calories 291 per serving.

title: valentine apple juice
directions: Combine apple juice, red hots and lemon juice in saucepan. Heat on low temperature.
Stir with wooden spoon until red hots are all melted.
Let cool a little and serve warm in cup.
Or chill and pour over ice in glass.

title: ribbon salad dessert
directions: Boil milk and add sugar.
Dissolve Knox in 1/2 cup water.
Add to milk and sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Beat with wire whisk until creamy.
Set aside.
(Do not refrigerate.)
Prepare 1st color Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate until set (about 30 minutes).
After set, pour in 1 1/2 cups white mixture and refrigerate until set.
Continue with other Jell-O and white mixture, beginning and ending with Jell-O.

title: no-cholesterol pear cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with Pam.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sugars, applesauce and egg whites.
Beat with a wooden spoon until well blended. Add flours, oat bran, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir until moistened. Stir in shredded pears.
Pour batter into the prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
You may add 1 cup chopped nuts, if preferred, before cooking.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Slice, salt and cook carrots until done; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Let stand overnight.

title: plain cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well.
Add milk and flour a little at a time.
Blend well.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring. Bake as layer cake or in a tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in a tube pan.
Bake layer cake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add eggs.
Beat smooth.
Add butter and rhubarb.
Pour into prepared 9-inch crust.
Top with top crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dried beef ball(a food processor recipe)
directions: Use steel cutting blade, shred one jar dried beef using speed 10.
Remove from bowl; set aside.
Add remaining jar dried beef, shred, then add cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, milk and horseradish.
Process at speed 4 until well mixed.
Place mixture on Saran Wrap, form into ball and roll in reserved dried beef. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Mix the soups and milk.
Pour rice in a bowl with 1 1/2 cups of the soup mixture.
Pour soup and rice mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put the chicken on the rice, then pour remaining soup mixture on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle a cup of Parmesan cheese on top and bake for 15 more minutes, uncovered.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat butter with the mixer. Add 1/2 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, egg, vanilla, baking soda and cream of tartar. Beat until combined. Beat in remaining flour. Refrigerate and chill for 1 hour. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon combined. Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes.

title: special k squares
directions: Mix the Karo syrup and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, but don't boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter and Special K cereal.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Spread on top.
Cool; cut into squares.
Excellent!!

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello, water and lemon juice.
Let cool.
Cream sugar and cheese together.
When jello is cool, add to cream cheese mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crust.
Use mixer.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Mix 1/2 jar salsa and beans together.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
